80namespace nlohmann {
81namespace detail {
83struct position_t {
85 std::size_t chars_read_total = 0;
87 std::size_t chars_read_current_line = 0;
89 std::size_t lines_read = 0;
90
92 constexpr operator size_t() const { return chars_read_total; }
93};

123#define JSON_HEDLEY_STRINGIFY_EX(x) #x

126#undef JSON_HEDLEY_STRINGIFY
127#endif
128#define JSON_HEDLEY_STRINGIFY(x) JSON_HEDLEY_STRINGIFY_EX(x)

131#undef JSON_HEDLEY_CONCAT_EX
132#endif
133#define JSON_HEDLEY_CONCAT_EX(a, b) a##b

136#undef JSON_HEDLEY_CONCAT
137#endif

140#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE)
141#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE
142#endif
143#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(major, minor, revision) (((major)*1000000) + ((minor)*1000) + (revision))
144
145#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MAJOR)
146#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MAJOR
147#endif
148#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MAJOR(version) ((version) / 1000000)
149
150#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MINOR)
151#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MINOR
152#endif
153#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_MINOR(version) (((version) % 1000000) / 1000)
154
155#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_REVISION)
156#undef JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_REVISION
157#endif
158#define JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_DECODE_REVISION(version) ((version) % 1000)
159
160#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION)
161#undef JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION
162#endif
163#if defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__)
164#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(__GNUC__, __GNUC_MINOR__, __GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__)
165#elif defined(__GNUC__)
166#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(__GNUC__, __GNUC_MINOR__, 0)
167#endif
168
169#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK)
170#undef JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK
171#endif
172#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION)
173#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK(major, minor, patch) \
174 (JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION >= JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(major, minor, patch))
175#else
176#define JSON_HEDLEY_GNUC_VERSION_CHECK(major, minor, patch) (0)
177#endif
178
179#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION)
180#undef JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION
181#endif
182#if defined(_MSC_FULL_VER) && (_MSC_FULL_VER >= 140000000)
183#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION \
184 JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(_MSC_FULL_VER / 10000000, (_MSC_FULL_VER % 10000000) / 100000, \
185 (_MSC_FULL_VER % 100000) / 100)
186#elif defined(_MSC_FULL_VER)
187#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION \
188 JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(_MSC_FULL_VER / 1000000, (_MSC_FULL_VER % 1000000) / 10000, (_MSC_FULL_VER % 10000) / 10)
189#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
190#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION JSON_HEDLEY_VERSION_ENCODE(_MSC_VER / 100, _MSC_VER % 100, 0)
191#endif
192
193#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK)
194#undef JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK
195#endif
196#if !defined(_MSC_VER)
197#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major, minor, patch) (0)
198#elif defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_VER >= 1400)
199#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major, minor, patch) \
200 (_MSC_FULL_VER >= ((major * 10000000) + (minor * 100000) + (patch)))
201#elif defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_VER >= 1200)
202#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major, minor, patch) \
203 (_MSC_FULL_VER >= ((major * 1000000) + (minor * 10000) + (patch)))
204#else
205#define JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(major, minor, patch) (_MSC_VER >= ((major * 100) + (minor)))
206#endif

846#if defined(__cplusplus) && (__cplusplus >= 201402L)
847#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED(since) JSON_HEDLEY_DIAGNOSTIC_DISABLE_CPP98_COMPAT_WRAP_([[deprecated("Since " #since)]])
848#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED_FOR(since, replacement) \
849 JSON_HEDLEY_DIAGNOSTIC_DISABLE_CPP98_COMPAT_WRAP_([[deprecated("Since " #since "; use " #replacement)]])
850#elif JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_EXTENSION(attribute_deprecated_with_message) || JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(4, 5, 0) || \
851 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(13, 0, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(5, 6, 0) || \
852 JSON_HEDLEY_SUNPRO_VERSION_CHECK(5, 13, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_PGI_VERSION_CHECK(17, 10, 0) || \
853 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_VERSION_CHECK(8, 3, 0)
854#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED(since) __attribute__((__deprecated__("Since " #since)))
855#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED_FOR(since, replacement) \
856 __attribute__((__deprecated__("Since " #since "; use " #replacement)))
857#elif JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_ATTRIBUTE(deprecated) || JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(3, 1, 0) || \
858 JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(4, 1, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_TI_VERSION_CHECK(8, 0, 0) || \
859 (JSON_HEDLEY_TI_VERSION_CHECK(7, 3, 0) && defined(__TI_GNU_ATTRIBUTE_SUPPORT__))
860#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED(since) __attribute__((__deprecated__))
861#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED_FOR(since, replacement) __attribute__((__deprecated__))
862#elif JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(14, 0, 0)
863#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED(since) __declspec(deprecated("Since " #since))
864#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED_FOR(since, replacement) __declspec(deprecated("Since " #since "; use " #replacement))
865#elif JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION_CHECK(13, 10, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_PELLES_VERSION_CHECK(6, 50, 0)
866#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED(since) __declspec(deprecated)
867#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED_FOR(since, replacement) __declspec(deprecated)
868#elif JSON_HEDLEY_IAR_VERSION_CHECK(8, 0, 0)
869#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED(since) _Pragma("deprecated")
870#define JSON_HEDLEY_DEPRECATED_FOR(since, replacement) _Pragma("deprecated")
871#else

1071#if JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_unpredictable)
1072#define JSON_HEDLEY_UNPREDICTABLE(expr) __builtin_unpredictable(!!(expr))
1073#endif
1074#if JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_expect_with_probability) || JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(9, 0, 0)
1075#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, value, probability) __builtin_expect_with_probability(expr, value, probability)
1076#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_TRUE(expr, probability) __builtin_expect_with_probability(!!(expr), 1, probability)
1077#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_FALSE(expr, probability) __builtin_expect_with_probability(!!(expr), 0, probability)
1078#define JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 1)
1079#define JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 0)
1080#if !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_BUILTIN_UNPREDICTABLE)
1081#define JSON_HEDLEY_BUILTIN_UNPREDICTABLE(expr) __builtin_expect_with_probability(!!(expr), 1, 0.5)
1082#endif
1083#elif JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_expect) || JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(3, 0, 0) || \
1084 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(13, 0, 0) || \
1085 (JSON_HEDLEY_SUNPRO_VERSION_CHECK(5, 15, 0) && defined(__cplusplus)) || JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(4, 1, 0) || \
1086 JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(10, 1, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_TI_VERSION_CHECK(6, 1, 0) || \
1087 JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION_CHECK(0, 9, 27)
1088#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, expected, probability) \
1089 (((probability) >= 0.9) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), (expected)) : (((void)(expected)), !!(expr)))
1090#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_TRUE(expr, probability) \
1091 (__extension__({ \
1092 JSON_HEDLEY_CONSTEXPR double hedley_probability_ = (probability); \
1093 ((hedley_probability_ >= 0.9) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 1) \
1094 : ((hedley_probability_ <= 0.1) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 0) : !!(expr))); \
1095 }))
1096#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_FALSE(expr, probability) \
1097 (__extension__({ \
1098 JSON_HEDLEY_CONSTEXPR double hedley_probability_ = (probability); \
1099 ((hedley_probability_ >= 0.9) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 0) \
1100 : ((hedley_probability_ <= 0.1) ? __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 1) : !!(expr))); \
1101 }))
1102#define JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 1)
1103#define JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(expr) __builtin_expect(!!(expr), 0)
1104#else
1105#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, expected, probability) (((void)(expected)), !!(expr))
1106#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_TRUE(expr, probability) (!!(expr))
1107#define JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT_FALSE(expr, probability) (!!(expr))
1108#define JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(expr) (!!(expr))
1109#define JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(expr) (!!(expr))
1110#endif
1111#if !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_UNPREDICTABLE)
1112#define JSON_HEDLEY_UNPREDICTABLE(expr) JSON_HEDLEY_PREDICT(expr, 1, 0.5)
1113#endif

1323/* JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_ is for
1324 HEDLEY INTERNAL USE ONLY. API subject to change without notice. */
1325#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_)
1326#undef JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_
1327#endif
1328#if JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_constant_p) || JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(3, 4, 0) || \
1329 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(13, 0, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION_CHECK(0, 9, 19) || \
1330 JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(4, 1, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(13, 1, 0) || \
1331 JSON_HEDLEY_TI_VERSION_CHECK(6, 1, 0) || (JSON_HEDLEY_SUNPRO_VERSION_CHECK(5, 10, 0) && !defined(__cplusplus)) || \
1332 JSON_HEDLEY_CRAY_VERSION_CHECK(8, 1, 0)
1333#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT(expr) __builtin_constant_p(expr)
1334#endif
1335#if !defined(__cplusplus)
1336#if JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_BUILTIN(__builtin_types_compatible_p) || JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(3, 4, 0) || \
1337 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(13, 0, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(13, 1, 0) || \
1338 JSON_HEDLEY_CRAY_VERSION_CHECK(8, 1, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(5, 4, 0) || \
1339 JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION_CHECK(0, 9, 24)
1340#if defined(__INTPTR_TYPE__)
1341#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) \
1342 __builtin_types_compatible_p(__typeof__((1 ? (void*)((__INTPTR_TYPE__)((expr)*0)) : (int*)0)), int*)
1343#else
1344#include <stdint.h>
1345#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) \
1346 __builtin_types_compatible_p(__typeof__((1 ? (void*)((intptr_t)((expr)*0)) : (int*)0)), int*)
1347#endif
1348#elif (defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && (__STDC_VERSION__ >= 201112L) && !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_SUNPRO_VERSION) && \
1349 !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_PGI_VERSION)) || \
1350 JSON_HEDLEY_HAS_EXTENSION(c_generic_selections) || JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION_CHECK(4, 9, 0) || \
1351 JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION_CHECK(17, 0, 0) || JSON_HEDLEY_IBM_VERSION_CHECK(12, 1, 0) || \
1352 JSON_HEDLEY_ARM_VERSION_CHECK(5, 3, 0)
1353#if defined(__INTPTR_TYPE__)
1354#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) \
1355 _Generic((1 ? (void*)((__INTPTR_TYPE__)((expr)*0)) : (int*)0), int* : 1, void* : 0)
1356#else
1357#include <stdint.h>
1358#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) _Generic((1 ? (void*)((intptr_t)*0) : (int*)0), int* : 1, void* : 0)
1359#endif
1360#elif defined(JSON_HEDLEY_GCC_VERSION) || defined(JSON_HEDLEY_INTEL_VERSION) || defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TINYC_VERSION) || \
1361 defined(JSON_HEDLEY_TI_VERSION) || defined(__clang__)
1362#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) \
1363 (sizeof(void) != sizeof(*(1 ? ((void*)((expr)*0L)) : ((struct { char v[sizeof(void) * 2]; }*)1))))
1364#endif
1365#endif
1366#if defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_)
1367#if !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT)
1368#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT(expr) JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr)
1369#endif
1370#define JSON_HEDLEY_REQUIRE_CONSTEXPR(expr) (JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTEXPR_(expr) ? (expr) : (-1))
1371#else
1372#if !defined(JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT)
1373#define JSON_HEDLEY_IS_CONSTANT(expr) (0)
1374#endif
1375#define JSON_HEDLEY_REQUIRE_CONSTEXPR(expr) (expr)
1376#endif

1689#define NLOHMANN_JSON_SERIALIZE_ENUM(ENUM_TYPE, ...) \
1690 template <typename BasicJsonType> \
1691 inline void to_json(BasicJsonType& j, const ENUM_TYPE& e) { \
1692 static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
1693 static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
1694 auto it = \
1695 std::find_if(std::begin(m), std::end(m), [e](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool { \
1696 return ej_pair.first == e; \
1697 }); \
1698 j = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->second; \
1699 } \
1700 template <typename BasicJsonType> \
1701 inline void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ENUM_TYPE& e) { \
1702 static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
1703 static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
1704 auto it = std::find_if( \
1705 std::begin(m), std::end(m), \
1706 [&j](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool { return ej_pair.second == j; }); \
1707 e = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->first; \
1708 }
1709
1710// Ugly macros to avoid uglier copy-paste when specializing basic_json. They
1711// may be removed in the future once the class is split.
1712
1713#define NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION \
1714 template <template <typename, typename, typename...> class ObjectType, \
1715 template <typename, typename...> class ArrayType, class StringType, class BooleanType, \
1716 class NumberIntegerType, class NumberUnsignedType, class NumberFloatType, \
1717 template <typename> class AllocatorType, template <typename, typename = void> class JSONSerializer>
1718
1719#define NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL \
1720 basic_json<ObjectType, ArrayType, StringType, BooleanType, NumberIntegerType, NumberUnsignedType, NumberFloatType, \
1721 AllocatorType, JSONSerializer>

1723namespace nlohmann {

1726// exceptions //
1728
1757class exception : public std::exception {
1758public:
1760 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
1761 const char* what() const noexcept override { return m.what(); }
1762
1764 const int id;
1765
1766protected:
1767 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
1768 exception(int id_, const char* what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {}
1769
1770 static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id_) {
1771 return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
1772 }
1773
1774private:
1776 std::runtime_error m;
1777};
1778
1835class parse_error : public exception {
1836public:
1846 static parse_error create(int id_, const position_t& pos, const std::string& what_arg) {
1847 std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" + position_string(pos) + ": " + what_arg;
1848 return parse_error(id_, pos.chars_read_total, w.c_str());
1849 }
1850
1851 static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg) {
1852 std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
1853 (byte_ != 0 ? (" at byte " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") + ": " + what_arg;
1854 return parse_error(id_, byte_, w.c_str());
1855 }
1856
1866 const std::size_t byte;
1867
1868private:
1869 parse_error(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const char* what_arg) : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_) {}
1870
1871 static std::string position_string(const position_t& pos) {
1872 return " at line " + std::to_string(pos.lines_read + 1) + ", column " +
1873 std::to_string(pos.chars_read_current_line);
1874 }
1875};
1876
1929class invalid_iterator : public exception {
1930public:
1931 static invalid_iterator create(int id_, const std::string& what_arg) {
1932 std::string w = exception::name("invalid_iterator", id_) + what_arg;
1933 return invalid_iterator(id_, w.c_str());
1934 }
1935
1936private:
1937 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
1938 invalid_iterator(int id_, const char* what_arg) : exception(id_, what_arg) {}
1939};

1992class type_error : public exception {
1993public:
1994 static type_error create(int id_, const std::string& what_arg) {
1995 std::string w = exception::name("type_error", id_) + what_arg;
1996 return type_error(id_, w.c_str());
1997 }
1998
1999private:
2000 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
2001 type_error(int id_, const char* what_arg) : exception(id_, what_arg) {}
2002};
2003
2041class out_of_range : public exception {
2042public:

2045 return out_of_range(id_, w.c_str());
2046 }
2047
2048private:
2049 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
2050 out_of_range(int id_, const char* what_arg) : exception(id_, what_arg) {}
2051};

2109// implementation of C++14 index_sequence and affiliates
2110// source: https://stackoverflow.com/a/32223343
2111template <std::size_t... Ints>
2112struct index_sequence {
2113 using type = index_sequence;
2114 using value_type = std::size_t;
2115 static constexpr std::size_t size() noexcept { return sizeof...(Ints); }
2116};
2117
2118template <class Sequence1, class Sequence2>
2119struct merge_and_renumber;
2120
2121template <std::size_t... I1, std::size_t... I2>
2122struct merge_and_renumber<index_sequence<I1...>, index_sequence<I2...>>
2123 : index_sequence<I1..., (sizeof...(I1) + I2)...> {};
2124
2125template <std::size_t N>
2126struct make_index_sequence
2127 : merge_and_renumber<typename make_index_sequence<N / 2>::type, typename make_index_sequence<N - N / 2>::type> {};
2128
2129template <>
2130struct make_index_sequence<0> : index_sequence<> {};
2131template <>
2132struct make_index_sequence<1> : index_sequence<0> {};
2133
2134template <typename... Ts>
2135using index_sequence_for = make_index_sequence<sizeof...(Ts)>;
2136
2137// dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
2138template <unsigned N>
2139struct priority_tag : priority_tag<N - 1> {};
2140template <>
2141struct priority_tag<0> {};
2142
2143// taken from ranges-v3
2144template <typename T>
2145struct static_const {
2146 static constexpr T value{};
2147};
2148
2149template <typename T>
2150constexpr T static_const<T>::value;

2187 typename It::reference, typename It::iterator_category>> {

2189 using value_type = typename It::value_type;

2192 using iterator_category = typename It::iterator_category;

2195// This is required as some compilers implement std::iterator_traits in a way that
2196// doesn't work with SFINAE. See https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1341.

2198struct iterator_traits {};

2208 using pointer = T*;
2209 using reference = T&;

2227struct nonesuch {
2228 nonesuch() = delete;
2229 ~nonesuch() = delete;
2230 nonesuch(nonesuch const&) = delete;
2231 nonesuch(nonesuch const&&) = delete;
2232 void operator=(nonesuch const&) = delete;

2236template <class Default, class AlwaysVoid, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2237struct detector {
2238 using value_t = std::false_type;
2239 using type = Default;
2240};
2241
2242template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2243struct detector<Default, void_t<Op<Args...>>, Op, Args...> {
2244 using value_t = std::true_type;
2245 using type = Op<Args...>;
2246};
2247
2248template <template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2249using is_detected = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::value_t;
2250
2251template <template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2252using detected_t = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::type;
2253
2254template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2255using detected_or = detector<Default, void, Op, Args...>;
2256
2257template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2258using detected_or_t = typename detected_or<Default, Op, Args...>::type;
2259
2260template <class Expected, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2261using is_detected_exact = std::is_same<Expected, detected_t<Op, Args...>>;
2262
2263template <class To, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
2264using is_detected_convertible = std::is_convertible<detected_t<Op, Args...>, To>;
2265} // namespace detail
2266} // namespace nlohmann

2342// Note to maintainers:
2343//
2344// Every trait in this file expects a non CV-qualified type.
2345// The only exceptions are in the 'aliases for detected' section
2346// (i.e. those of the form: decltype(T::member_function(std::declval<T>())))
2347//
2348// In this case, T has to be properly CV-qualified to constraint the function arguments
2349// (e.g. to_json(BasicJsonType&, const T&))
2350
2351template <typename>
2352struct is_basic_json : std::false_type {};
2353
2354NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
2355struct is_basic_json<NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL> : std::true_type {};
2356
2358// aliases for detected //
2360
2361template <typename T>
2362using mapped_type_t = typename T::mapped_type;
2363
2364template <typename T>
2365using key_type_t = typename T::key_type;
2366
2367template <typename T>
2368using value_type_t = typename T::value_type;
2369
2370template <typename T>
2371using difference_type_t = typename T::difference_type;
2372
2373template <typename T>
2374using pointer_t = typename T::pointer;
2375
2376template <typename T>
2377using reference_t = typename T::reference;
2378
2379template <typename T>
2380using iterator_category_t = typename T::iterator_category;
2381
2382template <typename T>
2383using iterator_t = typename T::iterator;
2384
2385template <typename T, typename... Args>
2386using to_json_function = decltype(T::to_json(std::declval<Args>()...));
2387
2388template <typename T, typename... Args>
2389using from_json_function = decltype(T::from_json(std::declval<Args>()...));
2390
2391template <typename T, typename U>
2392using get_template_function = decltype(std::declval<T>().template get<U>());

2394// trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
2395template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
2396struct has_from_json : std::false_type {};
2397
2398template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
2399struct has_from_json<BasicJsonType, T, enable_if_t<not is_basic_json<T>::value>> {
2400 using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
2401
2402 static constexpr bool value =
2403 is_detected_exact<void, from_json_function, serializer, const BasicJsonType&, T&>::value;
2404};
2405
2406// This trait checks if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&) exists
2407// this overload is used for non-default-constructible user-defined-types
2408template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
2409struct has_non_default_from_json : std::false_type {};
2410
2411template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
2412struct has_non_default_from_json<BasicJsonType, T, enable_if_t<not is_basic_json<T>::value>> {
2413 using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
2414
2415 static constexpr bool value = is_detected_exact<T, from_json_function, serializer, const BasicJsonType&>::value;
2416};
2417
2418// This trait checks if BasicJsonType::json_serializer<T>::to_json exists
2419// Do not evaluate the trait when T is a basic_json type, to avoid template instantiation infinite recursion.
2420template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
2421struct has_to_json : std::false_type {};
2422
2423template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
2424struct has_to_json<BasicJsonType, T, enable_if_t<not is_basic_json<T>::value>> {
2425 using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
2426
2427 static constexpr bool value = is_detected_exact<void, to_json_function, serializer, BasicJsonType&, T>::value;
2428};

2435struct is_iterator_traits : std::false_type {};
2436
2437template <typename T>
2438struct is_iterator_traits<iterator_traits<T>> {
2439private:
2440 using traits = iterator_traits<T>;
2441
2442public:
2443 static constexpr auto value =
2444 is_detected<value_type_t, traits>::value && is_detected<difference_type_t, traits>::value &&
2445 is_detected<pointer_t, traits>::value && is_detected<iterator_category_t, traits>::value &&
2446 is_detected<reference_t, traits>::value;
2447};

2457template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType, typename = void>
2458struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
2459
2460template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType>
2461struct is_compatible_object_type_impl<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType,
2462 enable_if_t<is_detected<mapped_type_t, CompatibleObjectType>::value and
2463 is_detected<key_type_t, CompatibleObjectType>::value>> {
2464
2465 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
2466
2467 // macOS's is_constructible does not play well with nonesuch...
2468 static constexpr bool value =
2469 std::is_constructible<typename object_t::key_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
2470 std::is_constructible<typename object_t::mapped_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
2471};
2472
2473template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType>
2474struct is_compatible_object_type : is_compatible_object_type_impl<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType> {};
2475
2476template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType, typename = void>
2477struct is_constructible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
2478
2479template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType>
2480struct is_constructible_object_type_impl<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleObjectType,
2481 enable_if_t<is_detected<mapped_type_t, ConstructibleObjectType>::value and
2482 is_detected<key_type_t, ConstructibleObjectType>::value>> {
2483 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
2484
2485 static constexpr bool value =
2486 (std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleObjectType>::value and
2487 (std::is_move_assignable<ConstructibleObjectType>::value or
2488 std::is_copy_assignable<ConstructibleObjectType>::value) and
2489 (std::is_constructible<typename ConstructibleObjectType::key_type, typename object_t::key_type>::value and
2490 std::is_same<typename object_t::mapped_type, typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value)) or
2491 (has_from_json<BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value or
2492 has_non_default_from_json<BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value);
2493};
2494
2495template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType>
2496struct is_constructible_object_type : is_constructible_object_type_impl<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleObjectType> {};

2525template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType, typename = void>
2526struct is_compatible_array_type_impl : std::false_type {};
2527
2528template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
2529struct is_compatible_array_type_impl<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType,
2530 enable_if_t<is_detected<value_type_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
2531 is_detected<iterator_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
2532 // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator
2533 // type... Therefore it is detected as a CompatibleArrayType. The real
2534 // fix would be to have an Iterable concept.
2535 not is_iterator_traits<iterator_traits<CompatibleArrayType>>::value>> {
2536 static constexpr bool value = std::is_constructible<BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>::value;
2537};
2538

2540struct is_compatible_array_type : is_compatible_array_type_impl<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType> {};
2541
2542template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType, typename = void>
2543struct is_constructible_array_type_impl : std::false_type {};
2544
2545template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
2546struct is_constructible_array_type_impl<
2547 BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
2548 enable_if_t<std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType, typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value>> : std::true_type {};
2549
2550template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
2551struct is_constructible_array_type_impl<
2552 BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
2553 enable_if_t<not std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType, typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value and
2554 std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
2555 (std::is_move_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value or
2556 std::is_copy_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value) and
2557 is_detected<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
2558 is_detected<iterator_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
2559 is_complete_type<detected_t<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType>>::value>> {
2560 static constexpr bool value =
2561 // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator type,
2562 // furthermore, std::back_insert_iterator (and other iterators) have a
2563 // base class `iterator`... Therefore it is detected as a
2564 // ConstructibleArrayType. The real fix would be to have an Iterable
2565 // concept.
2566 not is_iterator_traits<iterator_traits<ConstructibleArrayType>>::value and
2567
2568 (std::is_same<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type,
2569 typename BasicJsonType::array_t::value_type>::value or
2570 has_from_json<BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>::value or
2571 has_non_default_from_json<BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>::value);
2572};
2573
2574template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
2575struct is_constructible_array_type : is_constructible_array_type_impl<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType> {};

2580template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
2581struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl<
2582 RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType,
2583 enable_if_t<std::is_integral<RealIntegerType>::value and std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
2584 not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value>> {
2585 // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
2586 using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
2587 using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
2588
2589 static constexpr auto value = std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
2590 CompatibleLimits::is_integer and RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
2591};

2601 static constexpr bool value = has_to_json<BasicJsonType, CompatibleType>::value;
2602};

2607// https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/conjunction
2608template <class...>
2609struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
2610template <class B1>
2611struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
2612template <class B1, class... Bn>
2613struct conjunction<B1, Bn...> : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {};
2614
2615template <typename T1, typename T2>
2616struct is_constructible_tuple : std::false_type {};
2617
2618template <typename T1, typename... Args>
2619struct is_constructible_tuple<T1, std::tuple<Args...>> : conjunction<std::is_constructible<T1, Args>...> {};

2624
2625#include <array> // array

2631namespace nlohmann {
2632namespace detail {
2634// JSON type enumeration //
2636
2661enum class value_t : std::uint8_t {
2662 null,
2663 object,
2664 array,
2665 string,
2666 boolean,
2667 number_integer,
2668 number_unsigned,
2669 number_float,
2670 discarded
2671};
2672
2683inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept {
2684 static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 8> order = {{
2685 0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */, 1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */, 2 /* unsigned */,
2686 2 /* float */
2687 }};
2688
2689 const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
2690 const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
2691 return l_index < order.size() and r_index < order.size() and order[l_index] < order[r_index];
2692}
2693} // namespace detail
2694} // namespace nlohmann

2696namespace nlohmann {
2697namespace detail {
2698template <typename BasicJsonType>
2699void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename std::nullptr_t& n) {
2700 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_null())) {
2701 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be null, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2702 }
2703 n = nullptr;
2704}
2705
2706// overloads for basic_json template parameters
2707template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
2708 enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
2709 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
2710 int> = 0>
2711void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val) {
2712 switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
2713 case value_t::number_unsigned: {
2714 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
2715 break;
2716 }
2717 case value_t::number_integer: {
2718 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
2719 break;
2720 }
2721 case value_t::number_float: {
2722 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
2723 break;
2724 }
2725
2726 default:
2727 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2728 }
2729}
2730
2731template <typename BasicJsonType>
2732void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t& b) {
2733 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_boolean())) {
2734 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2735 }
2736 b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
2737}

2739template <typename BasicJsonType>
2740void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::string_t& s) {
2741 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_string())) {
2742 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be string, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2743 }
2744 s = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::string_t*>();
2745}

2747template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleStringType,
2748 enable_if_t<is_constructible_string_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleStringType>::value and
2749 not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::string_t, ConstructibleStringType>::value,
2750 int> = 0>
2751void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleStringType& s) {
2752 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_string())) {
2753 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be string, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2754 }
2755
2756 s = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::string_t*>();
2757}

2761 get_arithmetic_value(j, val);

2765void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t& val) {
2766 get_arithmetic_value(j, val);

2774template <typename BasicJsonType, typename EnumType, enable_if_t<std::is_enum<EnumType>::value, int> = 0>
2775void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, EnumType& e) {
2776 typename std::underlying_type<EnumType>::type val;
2777 get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
2778 e = static_cast<EnumType>(val);
2779}

2781// forward_list doesn't have an insert method
2782template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
2783 enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
2784void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l) {
2785 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
2786 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2787 }
2788 l.clear();
2789 std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(), std::front_inserter(l),
2790 [](const BasicJsonType& i) { return i.template get<T>(); });
2791}
2792
2793// valarray doesn't have an insert method
2794template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
2795void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::valarray<T>& l) {
2796 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
2797 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2798 }
2799 l.resize(j.size());
2800 std::copy(j.begin(), j.end(), std::begin(l));
2801}
2802
2803template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
2804auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, T (&arr)[N]) -> decltype(j.template get<T>(), void()) {
2805 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i) {
2806 arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
2807 }
2808}
2809
2810template <typename BasicJsonType>
2811void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t& arr, priority_tag<3> /*unused*/) {
2812 arr = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::array_t*>();
2813}
2814
2815template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
2816auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, std::array<T, N>& arr, priority_tag<2> /*unused*/)
2817 -> decltype(j.template get<T>(), void()) {
2818 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i) {
2819 arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
2820 }
2821}
2822
2823template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
2824auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
2825 -> decltype(arr.reserve(std::declval<typename ConstructibleArrayType::size_type>()),
2826 j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(), void()) {
2827 using std::end;
2828
2829 ConstructibleArrayType ret;
2830 ret.reserve(j.size());
2831 std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(ret, end(ret)), [](const BasicJsonType& i) {
2832 // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
2833 // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
2834 return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
2835 });
2836 arr = std::move(ret);
2837}
2838
2839template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
2840void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) {
2841 using std::end;
2842
2843 ConstructibleArrayType ret;
2844 std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(ret, end(ret)), [](const BasicJsonType& i) {
2845 // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
2846 // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
2847 return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
2848 });
2849 arr = std::move(ret);
2850}
2851
2852template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType,
2853 enable_if_t<is_constructible_array_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
2854 not is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
2855 not is_constructible_string_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
2856 not is_basic_json<ConstructibleArrayType>::value,
2857 int> = 0>
2858
2859auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr)
2860 -> decltype(from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3>{}),
2861 j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(), void()) {
2862 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
2863 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2864 }
2865
2866 from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3>{});
2867}
2868
2869template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType,
2870 enable_if_t<is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
2871void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleObjectType& obj) {
2872 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object())) {
2873 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2874 }
2875
2876 ConstructibleObjectType ret;
2877 auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
2878 using value_type = typename ConstructibleObjectType::value_type;
2879 std::transform(inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(), std::inserter(ret, ret.begin()),
2880 [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const& p) {
2881 return value_type(p.first,
2882 p.second.template get<typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
2883 });
2884 obj = std::move(ret);
2885}
2886
2887// overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
2888// (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
2889// overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
2890// an arithmetic type?
2891template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
2892 enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
2893 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
2894 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
2895 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
2896 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
2897 int> = 0>
2898void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val) {
2899 switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
2900 case value_t::number_unsigned: {
2901 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
2902 break;
2903 }
2904 case value_t::number_integer: {
2905 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
2906 break;
2907 }
2908 case value_t::number_float: {
2909 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
2910 break;
2911 }
2912 case value_t::boolean: {
2913 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
2914 break;
2915 }
2916
2917 default:
2918 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2919 }
2920}
2921
2922template <typename BasicJsonType, typename A1, typename A2>
2923void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::pair<A1, A2>& p) {
2924 p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};
2925}

2927template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
2928void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, Tuple& t, index_sequence<Idx...> /*unused*/) {
2929 t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
2930}
2931
2932template <typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
2933void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::tuple<Args...>& t) {
2934 from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...>{});
2935}

2937template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Compare, typename Allocator,
2938 typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
2939void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::map<Key, Value, Compare, Allocator>& m) {
2940 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
2941 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2942 }
2943 m.clear();
2944 for (const auto& p : j) {
2945 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array())) {
2946 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
2947 }
2948 m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
2949 }
2950}
2951
2952template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Hash, typename KeyEqual, typename Allocator,
2953 typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
2954void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::unordered_map<Key, Value, Hash, KeyEqual, Allocator>& m) {
2955 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
2956 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
2957 }
2958 m.clear();
2959 for (const auto& p : j) {
2960 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array())) {
2961 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
2962 }
2963 m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
2964 }
2965}
2966
2967struct from_json_fn {
2968 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
2969 auto operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
2970 -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void()) {
2971 return from_json(j, val);
2972 }
2973};
2974} // namespace detail

2980constexpr const auto& from_json = detail::static_const<detail::from_json_fn>::value;

3009template <typename string_type>
3010void int_to_string(string_type& target, std::size_t value) {
3011 target = std::to_string(value);
3012}
3013template <typename IteratorType>
3014class iteration_proxy_value {
3015public:
3016 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
3017 using value_type = iteration_proxy_value;
3018 using pointer = value_type*;
3019 using reference = value_type&;
3020 using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag;
3021 using string_type = typename std::remove_cv<
3022 typename std::remove_reference<decltype(std::declval<IteratorType>().key())>::type>::type;
3023
3024private:
3026 IteratorType anchor;
3028 std::size_t array_index = 0;
3030 mutable std::size_t array_index_last = 0;
3032 mutable string_type array_index_str = "0";
3034 const string_type empty_str = "";
3035
3036public:
3037 explicit iteration_proxy_value(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {}
3038
3040 iteration_proxy_value& operator*() { return *this; }
3041
3043 iteration_proxy_value& operator++() {
3044 ++anchor;
3045 ++array_index;
3046
3047 return *this;
3048 }
3049
3051 bool operator==(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const { return anchor == o.anchor; }
3052
3054 bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const { return anchor != o.anchor; }
3055
3057 const string_type& key() const {
3058 assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
3059
3060 switch (anchor.m_object->type()) {
3061 // use integer array index as key
3062 case value_t::array: {
3063 if (array_index != array_index_last) {
3064 int_to_string(array_index_str, array_index);
3065 array_index_last = array_index;
3066 }
3067 return array_index_str;
3068 }
3069
3070 // use key from the object
3071 case value_t::object:
3072 return anchor.key();
3073
3074 // use an empty key for all primitive types
3075 default:
3076 return empty_str;
3077 }
3078 }
3079
3081 typename IteratorType::reference value() const { return anchor.value(); }
3082};
3083
3085template <typename IteratorType>
3086class iteration_proxy {
3087private:
3089 typename IteratorType::reference container;
3090
3091public:
3093 explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept : container(cont) {}
3094
3096 iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> begin() noexcept {
3097 return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.begin());
3098 }
3099
3101 iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> end() noexcept { return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.end()); }
3102};
3103// Structured Bindings Support
3104// For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
3105// And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
3106template <std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 0, int> = 0>
3107auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.key()) {
3108 return i.key();
3109}
3110// Structured Bindings Support
3111// For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
3112// And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
3113template <std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 1, int> = 0>
3114auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.value()) {
3115 return i.value();
3116}
3117} // namespace detail

3162 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t b) noexcept {
3163 j.m_type = value_t::boolean;
3164 j.m_value = b;
3165 j.assert_invariant();
3166 }

3173 j.m_type = value_t::string;
3174 j.m_value = s;
3175 j.assert_invariant();
3176 }

3179 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::string_t&& s) {
3180 j.m_type = value_t::string;
3181 j.m_value = std::move(s);
3182 j.assert_invariant();

3187 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleStringType& str) {
3188 j.m_type = value_t::string;
3189 j.m_value.string = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::string_t>(str);
3190 j.assert_invariant();
3191 }

3243 using std::begin;
3244 using std::end;

3250 template <typename BasicJsonType>
3251 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::vector<bool>& arr) {
3252 j.m_type = value_t::array;
3253 j.m_value = value_t::array;
3254 j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
3255 for (const bool x : arr) {
3256 j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
3257 }
3258 j.assert_invariant();
3259 }
3260
3261 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<T, BasicJsonType>::value, int> = 0>
3262 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::valarray<T>& arr) {
3263 j.m_type = value_t::array;
3264 j.m_value = value_t::array;
3265 j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
3266 if (arr.size() > 0) {
3267 std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
3268 }
3269 j.assert_invariant();
3270 }
3271};
3272
3273template <>
3274struct external_constructor<value_t::object> {
3275 template <typename BasicJsonType>
3276 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& obj) {
3277 j.m_type = value_t::object;
3278 j.m_value = obj;
3279 j.assert_invariant();
3280 }
3281
3282 template <typename BasicJsonType>
3283 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::object_t&& obj) {
3284 j.m_type = value_t::object;
3285 j.m_value = std::move(obj);
3286 j.assert_invariant();
3287 }
3288
3289 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
3290 enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleObjectType, typename BasicJsonType::object_t>::value, int> = 0>
3291 static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleObjectType& obj) {
3292 using std::begin;
3293 using std::end;
3294
3295 j.m_type = value_t::object;
3296 j.m_value.object = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::object_t>(begin(obj), end(obj));
3297 j.assert_invariant();
3298 }
3299};

3420struct to_json_fn {
3421 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
3422 auto operator()(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val) const noexcept(noexcept(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val))))
3423 -> decltype(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)), void()) {
3424 return to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val));
3425 }
3426};

3437template <typename, typename>
3438struct adl_serializer {
3448 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ValueType>
3449 static auto from_json(BasicJsonType&& j,
3450 ValueType& val) noexcept(noexcept(::nlohmann::from_json(std::forward<BasicJsonType>(j), val)))
3451 -> decltype(::nlohmann::from_json(std::forward<BasicJsonType>(j), val), void()) {
3452 ::nlohmann::from_json(std::forward<BasicJsonType>(j), val);
3453 }
3454
3464 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ValueType>
3465 static auto to_json(BasicJsonType& j,
3466 ValueType&& val) noexcept(noexcept(::nlohmann::to_json(j, std::forward<ValueType>(val))))
3467 -> decltype(::nlohmann::to_json(j, std::forward<ValueType>(val)), void()) {
3468 ::nlohmann::to_json(j, std::forward<ValueType>(val));
3469 }
3470};

3522// input adapters //
3524
3536struct input_adapter_protocol {
3538 virtual std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() = 0;
3539 virtual ~input_adapter_protocol() = default;
3540};
3541
3543using input_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<input_adapter_protocol>;
3544
3549class file_input_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol {
3550public:
3551 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
3552 explicit file_input_adapter(std::FILE* f) noexcept : m_file(f) {}
3553
3554 // make class move-only
3555 file_input_adapter(const file_input_adapter&) = delete;
3556 file_input_adapter(file_input_adapter&&) = default;
3557 file_input_adapter& operator=(const file_input_adapter&) = delete;
3558 file_input_adapter& operator=(file_input_adapter&&) = default;
3559 ~file_input_adapter() override = default;
3560
3561 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override { return std::fgetc(m_file); }
3562
3563private:
3565 std::FILE* m_file;
3566};
3567
3577class input_stream_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol {
3578public:
3579 ~input_stream_adapter() override {
3580 // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
3581 // maintain ifstream flags, except eof
3582 is.clear(is.rdstate() & std::ios::eofbit);
3583 }
3584
3585 explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i) : is(i), sb(*i.rdbuf()) {}
3586
3587 // delete because of pointer members
3588 input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
3589 input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
3590 input_stream_adapter(input_stream_adapter&&) = delete;
3591 input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&&) = delete;
3592
3593 // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
3594 // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
3595 // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
3596 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() override {
3597 auto res = sb.sbumpc();
3598 // set eof manually, as we don't use the istream interface.
3599 if (res == EOF) {
3600 is.clear(is.rdstate() | std::ios::eofbit);
3601 }
3602 return res;
3603 }
3604
3605private:
3607 std::istream& is;
3608 std::streambuf& sb;
3609};
3610
3612class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol {
3613public:
3614 input_buffer_adapter(const char* b, const std::size_t l) noexcept
3615 : cursor(b), limit(b == nullptr ? nullptr : (b + l)) {}
3616
3617 // delete because of pointer members
3618 input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
3619 input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
3620 input_buffer_adapter(input_buffer_adapter&&) = delete;
3621 input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&&) = delete;
3622 ~input_buffer_adapter() override = default;
3623
3624 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override {
3625 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(cursor < limit)) {
3626 assert(cursor != nullptr and limit != nullptr);
3627 return std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type(*(cursor++));
3628 }
3629
3630 return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
3631 }
3632
3633private:
3635 const char* cursor;
3637 const char* const limit;
3638};
3639
3640template <typename WideStringType, size_t T>
3641struct wide_string_input_helper {
3642 // UTF-32
3643 static void fill_buffer(const WideStringType& str, size_t& current_wchar,
3644 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes, size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
3645 size_t& utf8_bytes_filled) {
3646 utf8_bytes_index = 0;
3647
3648 if (current_wchar == str.size()) {
3649 utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
3650 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
3651 } else {
3652 // get the current character
3653 const auto wc = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
3654
3655 // UTF-32 to UTF-8 encoding
3656 if (wc < 0x80) {
3657 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
3658 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
3659 } else if (wc <= 0x7FF) {
3660 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x1Fu));
3661 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
3662 utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
3663 } else if (wc <= 0xFFFF) {
3664 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((wc >> 12u) & 0x0Fu));
3665 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
3666 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
3667 utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
3668 } else if (wc <= 0x10FFFF) {
3669 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | ((wc >> 18u) & 0x07u));
3670 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
3671 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
3672 utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
3673 utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
3674 } else {
3675 // unknown character
3676 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
3677 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
3678 }
3679 }
3680 }
3681};
3682
3683template <typename WideStringType>
3684struct wide_string_input_helper<WideStringType, 2> {
3685 // UTF-16
3686 static void fill_buffer(const WideStringType& str, size_t& current_wchar,
3687 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes, size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
3688 size_t& utf8_bytes_filled) {
3689 utf8_bytes_index = 0;
3690
3691 if (current_wchar == str.size()) {
3692 utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
3693 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
3694 } else {
3695 // get the current character
3696 const auto wc = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
3697
3698 // UTF-16 to UTF-8 encoding
3699 if (wc < 0x80) {
3700 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
3701 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
3702 } else if (wc <= 0x7FF) {
3703 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((wc >> 6u)));
3704 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
3705 utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
3706 } else if (0xD800 > wc or wc >= 0xE000) {
3707 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((wc >> 12u)));
3708 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
3709 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
3710 utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
3711 } else {
3712 if (current_wchar < str.size()) {
3713 const auto wc2 = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
3714 const auto charcode = 0x10000u + (((wc & 0x3FFu) << 10u) | (wc2 & 0x3FFu));
3715 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | (charcode >> 18u));
3716 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
3717 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
3718 utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (charcode & 0x3Fu));
3719 utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
3720 } else {
3721 // unknown character
3722 ++current_wchar;
3723 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
3724 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
3725 }
3726 }
3727 }
3728 }
3729};
3730
3731template <typename WideStringType>
3732class wide_string_input_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol {
3733public:
3734 explicit wide_string_input_adapter(const WideStringType& w) noexcept : str(w) {}
3735
3736 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override {
3737 // check if buffer needs to be filled
3738 if (utf8_bytes_index == utf8_bytes_filled) {
3739 fill_buffer<sizeof(typename WideStringType::value_type)>();
3740
3741 assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
3742 assert(utf8_bytes_index == 0);
3743 }
3744
3745 // use buffer
3746 assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
3747 assert(utf8_bytes_index < utf8_bytes_filled);
3748 return utf8_bytes[utf8_bytes_index++];
3749 }
3750
3751private:
3752 template <size_t T>
3753 void fill_buffer() {
3754 wide_string_input_helper<WideStringType, T>::fill_buffer(str, current_wchar, utf8_bytes, utf8_bytes_index,
3755 utf8_bytes_filled);
3756 }
3757
3759 const WideStringType& str;
3760
3762 std::size_t current_wchar = 0;
3763
3765 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4> utf8_bytes = {{0, 0, 0, 0}};
3766
3768 std::size_t utf8_bytes_index = 0;
3770 std::size_t utf8_bytes_filled = 0;
3771};
3772
3773class input_adapter {
3774public:
3775 // native support
3776 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
3777 input_adapter(std::FILE* file) : ia(std::make_shared<file_input_adapter>(file)) {}
3779 input_adapter(std::istream& i) : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
3780
3782 input_adapter(std::istream&& i) : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
3783
3784 input_adapter(const std::wstring& ws) : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::wstring>>(ws)) {}
3785
3786 input_adapter(const std::u16string& ws) : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u16string>>(ws)) {}
3787
3788 input_adapter(const std::u32string& ws) : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u32string>>(ws)) {}
3789
3791 template <typename CharT,
3792 typename std::enable_if<std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
3793 std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
3794 sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
3795 int>::type = 0>
3796 input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
3797 : ia(std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), l)) {}
3798
3799 // derived support
3800
3802 template <typename CharT,
3803 typename std::enable_if<std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
3804 std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
3805 sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
3806 int>::type = 0>
3807 input_adapter(CharT b)
3808 : input_adapter(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b))) {}
3809
3811 template <class IteratorType,
3812 typename std::enable_if<std::is_same<typename iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category,
3813 std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
3814 int>::type = 0>
3815 input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last) {
3816#ifndef NDEBUG
3817 // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
3818 // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
3819 const auto is_contiguous = std::accumulate(first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
3820 [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val) {
3821 res.first &=
3822 (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
3823 return res;
3824 })
3825 .first;
3826 assert(is_contiguous);
3827#endif
3828
3829 // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
3830 static_assert(sizeof(typename iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
3831 "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
3832
3833 const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last));
3834 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(len > 0)) {
3835 // there is at least one element: use the address of first
3836 ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&(*first)), len);
3837 } else {
3838 // the address of first cannot be used: use nullptr
3839 ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(nullptr, len);
3840 }
3841 }
3842
3844 template <class T, std::size_t N>
3845 input_adapter(T (&array)[N]) : input_adapter(std::begin(array), std::end(array)) {}
3846
3848 template <class ContiguousContainer,
3849 typename std::enable_if<
3850 not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
3851 std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag,
3852 typename iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(
3853 std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value,
3854 int>::type = 0>
3855 input_adapter(const ContiguousContainer& c) : input_adapter(std::begin(c), std::end(c)) {}
3856
3857 operator input_adapter_t() { return ia; }
3858
3859private:
3861 input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
3862};
3863} // namespace detail
3864} // namespace nlohmann

3888template <typename BasicJsonType>
3889struct json_sax {
3891 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3893 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3895 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3897 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3898
3903 virtual bool null() = 0;
3904
3910 virtual bool boolean(bool val) = 0;
3911
3917 virtual bool number_integer(number_integer_t val) = 0;
3918
3924 virtual bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val) = 0;
3925
3932 virtual bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& s) = 0;
3933
3940 virtual bool string(string_t& val) = 0;
3941
3948 virtual bool start_object(std::size_t elements) = 0;
3949
3956 virtual bool key(string_t& val) = 0;
3957
3962 virtual bool end_object() = 0;
3963
3970 virtual bool start_array(std::size_t elements) = 0;
3971
3976 virtual bool end_array() = 0;
3977
3985 virtual bool parse_error(std::size_t position, const std::string& last_token, const detail::exception& ex) = 0;
3986
3987 virtual ~json_sax() = default;
3988};

3990namespace detail {
4004template <typename BasicJsonType>
4005class json_sax_dom_parser {
4006public:
4007 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4008 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4009 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4010 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4011
4017 explicit json_sax_dom_parser(BasicJsonType& r, const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
4018 : root(r), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_) {}
4019
4020 // make class move-only
4021 json_sax_dom_parser(const json_sax_dom_parser&) = delete;
4022 json_sax_dom_parser(json_sax_dom_parser&&) = default;
4023 json_sax_dom_parser& operator=(const json_sax_dom_parser&) = delete;
4024 json_sax_dom_parser& operator=(json_sax_dom_parser&&) = default;
4025 ~json_sax_dom_parser() = default;
4026
4027 bool null() {
4028 handle_value(nullptr);
4029 return true;
4030 }
4031
4032 bool boolean(bool val) {
4033 handle_value(val);
4034 return true;
4035 }
4036
4037 bool number_integer(number_integer_t val) {
4038 handle_value(val);
4039 return true;
4040 }
4041
4042 bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val) {
4043 handle_value(val);
4044 return true;
4045 }
4046
4047 bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& /*unused*/) {
4048 handle_value(val);
4049 return true;
4050 }
4051
4052 bool string(string_t& val) {
4053 handle_value(val);
4054 return true;
4055 }
4056
4057 bool start_object(std::size_t len) {
4058 ref_stack.push_back(handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object));
4059
4060 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size())) {
4061 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
4062 }
4063
4064 return true;
4065 }
4066
4067 bool key(string_t& val) {
4068 // add null at given key and store the reference for later
4069 object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val));
4070 return true;
4071 }
4072
4073 bool end_object() {
4074 ref_stack.pop_back();
4075 return true;
4076 }
4077
4078 bool start_array(std::size_t len) {
4079 ref_stack.push_back(handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array));
4080
4081 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size())) {
4082 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
4083 }
4084
4085 return true;
4086 }
4087
4088 bool end_array() {
4089 ref_stack.pop_back();
4090 return true;
4091 }
4092
4093 bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/, const detail::exception& ex) {
4094 errored = true;
4095 if (allow_exceptions) {
4096 // determine the proper exception type from the id
4097 switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100) {
4098 case 1:
4099 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
4100 case 4:
4101 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
4102 // LCOV_EXCL_START
4103 case 2:
4104 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex));
4105 case 3:
4106 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex));
4107 case 5:
4108 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex));
4109 default:
4110 assert(false);
4111 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
4112 }
4113 }
4114 return false;
4115 }
4116
4117 constexpr bool is_errored() const { return errored; }
4118
4119private:
4126 template <typename Value>
4127 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL BasicJsonType* handle_value(Value&& v) {
4128 if (ref_stack.empty()) {
4129 root = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
4130 return &root;
4131 }
4132
4133 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
4134
4135 if (ref_stack.back()->is_array()) {
4136 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->emplace_back(std::forward<Value>(v));
4137 return &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back());
4138 }
4139
4140 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
4141 assert(object_element);
4142 *object_element = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
4143 return object_element;
4144 }
4145
4147 BasicJsonType& root;
4149 std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack{};
4151 BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
4153 bool errored = false;
4155 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
4156};
4157
4158template <typename BasicJsonType>
4159class json_sax_dom_callback_parser {
4160public:
4161 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4162 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4163 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4164 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4165 using parser_callback_t = typename BasicJsonType::parser_callback_t;
4166 using parse_event_t = typename BasicJsonType::parse_event_t;
4167
4168 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(BasicJsonType& r, const parser_callback_t cb, const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
4169 : root(r), callback(cb), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_) {
4170 keep_stack.push_back(true);
4171 }
4172
4173 // make class move-only
4174 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
4175 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
4176 json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
4177 json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
4178 ~json_sax_dom_callback_parser() = default;
4179
4180 bool null() {
4181 handle_value(nullptr);
4182 return true;
4183 }
4184
4185 bool boolean(bool val) {
4186 handle_value(val);
4187 return true;
4188 }
4189
4190 bool number_integer(number_integer_t val) {
4191 handle_value(val);
4192 return true;
4193 }
4194
4195 bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val) {
4196 handle_value(val);
4197 return true;
4198 }
4199
4200 bool number_float(number_float_t val, const string_t& /*unused*/) {
4201 handle_value(val);
4202 return true;
4203 }
4204
4205 bool string(string_t& val) {
4206 handle_value(val);
4207 return true;
4208 }
4209
4210 bool start_object(std::size_t len) {
4211 // check callback for object start
4212 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::object_start, discarded);
4213 keep_stack.push_back(keep);
4214
4215 auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object, true);
4216 ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
4217
4218 // check object limit
4219 if (ref_stack.back() and JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size())) {
4220 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
4221 }
4222
4223 return true;
4224 }
4225
4226 bool key(string_t& val) {
4227 BasicJsonType k = BasicJsonType(val);
4228
4229 // check callback for key
4230 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::key, k);
4231 key_keep_stack.push_back(keep);
4232
4233 // add discarded value at given key and store the reference for later
4234 if (keep and ref_stack.back()) {
4235 object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val) = discarded);
4236 }
4237
4238 return true;
4239 }
4240
4241 bool end_object() {
4242 if (ref_stack.back() and
4243 not callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::object_end, *ref_stack.back())) {
4244 // discard object
4245 *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
4246 }
4247
4248 assert(not ref_stack.empty());
4249 assert(not keep_stack.empty());
4250 ref_stack.pop_back();
4251 keep_stack.pop_back();
4252
4253 if (not ref_stack.empty() and ref_stack.back() and ref_stack.back()->is_object()) {
4254 // remove discarded value
4255 for (auto it = ref_stack.back()->begin(); it != ref_stack.back()->end(); ++it) {
4256 if (it->is_discarded()) {
4257 ref_stack.back()->erase(it);
4258 break;
4259 }
4260 }
4261 }
4262
4263 return true;
4264 }
4265
4266 bool start_array(std::size_t len) {
4267 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::array_start, discarded);
4268 keep_stack.push_back(keep);
4269
4270 auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array, true);
4271 ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
4272
4273 // check array limit
4274 if (ref_stack.back() and JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size())) {
4275 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
4276 }
4277
4278 return true;
4279 }
4280
4281 bool end_array() {
4282 bool keep = true;
4283
4284 if (ref_stack.back()) {
4285 keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::array_end, *ref_stack.back());
4286 if (not keep) {
4287 // discard array
4288 *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
4289 }
4290 }
4291
4292 assert(not ref_stack.empty());
4293 assert(not keep_stack.empty());
4294 ref_stack.pop_back();
4295 keep_stack.pop_back();
4296
4297 // remove discarded value
4298 if (not keep and not ref_stack.empty() and ref_stack.back()->is_array()) {
4299 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->pop_back();
4300 }
4301
4302 return true;
4303 }
4304
4305 bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/, const detail::exception& ex) {
4306 errored = true;
4307 if (allow_exceptions) {
4308 // determine the proper exception type from the id
4309 switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100) {
4310 case 1:
4311 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
4312 case 4:
4313 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
4314 // LCOV_EXCL_START
4315 case 2:
4316 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex));
4317 case 3:
4318 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex));
4319 case 5:
4320 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex));
4321 default:
4322 assert(false);
4323 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
4324 }
4325 }
4326 return false;
4327 }
4328
4329 constexpr bool is_errored() const { return errored; }
4330
4331private:
4347 template <typename Value>
4348 std::pair<bool, BasicJsonType*> handle_value(Value&& v, const bool skip_callback = false) {
4349 assert(not keep_stack.empty());
4350
4351 // do not handle this value if we know it would be added to a discarded
4352 // container
4353 if (not keep_stack.back()) {
4354 return {false, nullptr};
4355 }
4356
4357 // create value
4358 auto value = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
4359
4360 // check callback
4361 const bool keep = skip_callback or callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::value, value);
4362
4363 // do not handle this value if we just learnt it shall be discarded
4364 if (not keep) {
4365 return {false, nullptr};
4366 }
4367
4368 if (ref_stack.empty()) {
4369 root = std::move(value);
4370 return {true, &root};
4371 }
4372
4373 // skip this value if we already decided to skip the parent
4374 // (https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/971#issuecomment-413678360)
4375 if (not ref_stack.back()) {
4376 return {false, nullptr};
4377 }
4378
4379 // we now only expect arrays and objects
4380 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
4381
4382 // array
4383 if (ref_stack.back()->is_array()) {
4384 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
4385 return {true, &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back())};
4386 }
4387
4388 // object
4389 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
4390 // check if we should store an element for the current key
4391 assert(not key_keep_stack.empty());
4392 const bool store_element = key_keep_stack.back();
4393 key_keep_stack.pop_back();
4394
4395 if (not store_element) {
4396 return {false, nullptr};
4397 }
4398
4399 assert(object_element);
4400 *object_element = std::move(value);
4401 return {true, object_element};
4402 }
4403
4405 BasicJsonType& root;
4407 std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack{};
4409 std::vector<bool> keep_stack{};
4411 std::vector<bool> key_keep_stack{};
4413 BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
4415 bool errored = false;
4417 const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
4419 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
4421 BasicJsonType discarded = BasicJsonType::value_t::discarded;
4422};
4423
4424template <typename BasicJsonType>
4425class json_sax_acceptor {
4426public:
4427 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4428 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4429 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4430 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4431
4432 bool null() { return true; }
4433
4434 bool boolean(bool /*unused*/) { return true; }
4435
4436 bool number_integer(number_integer_t /*unused*/) { return true; }
4437
4438 bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t /*unused*/) { return true; }
4439
4440 bool number_float(number_float_t /*unused*/, const string_t& /*unused*/) { return true; }
4441
4442 bool string(string_t& /*unused*/) { return true; }
4443
4444 bool start_object(std::size_t /*unused*/ = std::size_t(-1)) { return true; }
4445
4446 bool key(string_t& /*unused*/) { return true; }
4447
4448 bool end_object() { return true; }
4449
4450 bool start_array(std::size_t /*unused*/ = std::size_t(-1)) { return true; }
4451
4452 bool end_array() { return true; }
4453
4454 bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/, const detail::exception& /*unused*/) {
4455 return false;
4456 }
4457};

4468#include <utility> // declval
