4475namespace detail {
4476template <typename T>
4477using null_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().null());
4478
4479template <typename T>
4480using boolean_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().boolean(std::declval<bool>()));
4481
4482template <typename T, typename Integer>
4483using number_integer_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_integer(std::declval<Integer>()));
4484
4485template <typename T, typename Unsigned>
4486using number_unsigned_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_unsigned(std::declval<Unsigned>()));
4487
4488template <typename T, typename Float, typename String>
4489using number_float_function_t =
4490 decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_float(std::declval<Float>(), std::declval<const String&>()));
4491
4492template <typename T, typename String>
4493using string_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().string(std::declval<String&>()));
4494
4495template <typename T>
4496using start_object_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_object(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
4497
4498template <typename T, typename String>
4499using key_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().key(std::declval<String&>()));
4500
4501template <typename T>
4502using end_object_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_object());
4503
4504template <typename T>
4505using start_array_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_array(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
4506
4507template <typename T>
4508using end_array_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_array());
4509
4510template <typename T, typename Exception>
4511using parse_error_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().parse_error(
4512 std::declval<std::size_t>(), std::declval<const std::string&>(), std::declval<const Exception&>()));
4513
4514template <typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
4515struct is_sax {
4516private:
4517 static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value, "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
4518
4519 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4520 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4521 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4522 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4523 using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
4524
4525public:
4526 static constexpr bool value =
4527 is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value &&
4528 is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value &&
4529 is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX, number_integer_t>::value &&
4530 is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX, number_unsigned_t>::value &&
4531 is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX, number_float_t, string_t>::value &&
4532 is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
4533 is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
4534 is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
4535 is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
4536 is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
4537 is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
4538 is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value;
4539};
4540
4541template <typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
4542struct is_sax_static_asserts {
4543private:
4544 static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value, "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
4545
4546 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4547 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4548 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4549 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4550 using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
4551
4552public:
4553 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value, "Missing/invalid function: bool null()");
4554 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
4555 "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
4556 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
4557 "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
4558 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX, number_integer_t>::value,
4559 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_integer(number_integer_t)");
4560 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX, number_unsigned_t>::value,
4561 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t)");
4562 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX, number_float_t, string_t>::value,
4563 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_float(number_float_t, const string_t&)");
4564 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
4565 "Missing/invalid function: bool string(string_t&)");
4566 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
4567 "Missing/invalid function: bool start_object(std::size_t)");
4568 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
4569 "Missing/invalid function: bool key(string_t&)");
4570 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
4571 "Missing/invalid function: bool end_object()");
4572 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
4573 "Missing/invalid function: bool start_array(std::size_t)");
4574 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
4575 "Missing/invalid function: bool end_array()");
4576 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value,
4577 "Missing/invalid function: bool parse_error(std::size_t, const "
4578 "std::string&, const exception&)");
4579};
4580} // namespace detail

4588// binary reader //
4590
4594template <typename BasicJsonType, typename SAX = json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType>>
4595class binary_reader {
4596 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
4597 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
4598 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
4599 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
4600 using json_sax_t = SAX;
4601
4602public:
4608 explicit binary_reader(input_adapter_t adapter) : ia(std::move(adapter)) {
4609 (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType>{};
4610 assert(ia);
4611 }
4612
4613 // make class move-only
4614 binary_reader(const binary_reader&) = delete;
4615 binary_reader(binary_reader&&) = default;
4616 binary_reader& operator=(const binary_reader&) = delete;
4617 binary_reader& operator=(binary_reader&&) = default;
4618 ~binary_reader() = default;
4619
4627 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
4628 bool sax_parse(const input_format_t format, json_sax_t* sax_, const bool strict = true) {
4629 sax = sax_;
4630 bool result = false;
4631
4632 switch (format) {
4633 case input_format_t::bson:
4634 result = parse_bson_internal();
4635 break;
4636
4637 case input_format_t::cbor:
4638 result = parse_cbor_internal();
4639 break;
4640
4641 case input_format_t::msgpack:
4642 result = parse_msgpack_internal();
4643 break;
4644
4645 case input_format_t::ubjson:
4646 result = parse_ubjson_internal();
4647 break;
4648
4649 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4650 assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
4651 }
4652
4653 // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
4654 if (result and strict) {
4655 if (format == input_format_t::ubjson) {
4656 get_ignore_noop();
4657 } else {
4658 get();
4659 }
4660
4661 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
4662 return sax->parse_error(
4663 chars_read, get_token_string(),
4664 parse_error::create(110, chars_read,
4665 exception_message(format,
4666 "expected end of input; last byte: 0x" + get_token_string(),
4667 "value")));
4668 }
4669 }
4670
4671 return result;
4672 }
4673
4681 static constexpr bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept { return *reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1; }
4682
4683private:
4685 // BSON //
4687
4692 bool parse_bson_internal() {
4693 std::int32_t document_size;
4694 get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
4695
4696 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1)))) {
4697 return false;
4698 }
4699
4700 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/ false))) {
4701 return false;
4702 }
4703
4704 return sax->end_object();
4705 }
4706
4714 bool get_bson_cstr(string_t& result) {
4715 auto out = std::back_inserter(result);
4716 while (true) {
4717 get();
4718 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "cstring"))) {
4719 return false;
4720 }
4721 if (current == 0x00) {
4722 return true;
4723 }
4724 *out++ = static_cast<char>(current);
4725 }
4726
4727 return true;
4728 }
4729
4741 template <typename NumberType>
4742 bool get_bson_string(const NumberType len, string_t& result) {
4743 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len < 1)) {
4744 auto last_token = get_token_string();
4745 return sax->parse_error(
4746 chars_read, last_token,
4747 parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
4748 exception_message(input_format_t::bson,
4749 "string length must be at least 1, is " + std::to_string(len),
4750 "string")));
4751 }
4752
4753 return get_string(input_format_t::bson, len - static_cast<NumberType>(1), result) and
4754 get() != std::char_traits<char>::eof();
4755 }
4756
4767 bool parse_bson_element_internal(const int element_type, const std::size_t element_type_parse_position) {
4768 switch (element_type) {
4769 case 0x01: // double
4770 {
4771 double number;
4772 return get_number<double, true>(input_format_t::bson, number) and
4773 sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
4774 }
4775
4776 case 0x02: // string
4777 {
4778 std::int32_t len;
4779 string_t value;
4780 return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, len) and get_bson_string(len, value) and
4781 sax->string(value);
4782 }
4783
4784 case 0x03: // object
4785 {
4786 return parse_bson_internal();
4787 }
4788
4789 case 0x04: // array
4790 {
4791 return parse_bson_array();
4792 }
4793
4794 case 0x08: // boolean
4795 {
4796 return sax->boolean(get() != 0);
4797 }
4798
4799 case 0x0A: // null
4800 {
4801 return sax->null();
4802 }
4803
4804 case 0x10: // int32
4805 {
4806 std::int32_t value;
4807 return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) and sax->number_integer(value);
4808 }
4809
4810 case 0x12: // int64
4811 {
4812 std::int64_t value;
4813 return get_number<std::int64_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) and sax->number_integer(value);
4814 }
4815
4816 default: // anything else not supported (yet)
4817 {
4818 std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
4819 (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(element_type));
4820 return sax->parse_error(element_type_parse_position, std::string(cr.data()),
4821 parse_error::create(114, element_type_parse_position,
4822 "Unsupported BSON record type 0x" + std::string(cr.data())));
4823 }
4824 }
4825 }
4826
4839 bool parse_bson_element_list(const bool is_array) {
4840 string_t key;
4841 while (int element_type = get()) {
4842 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "element list"))) {
4843 return false;
4844 }
4845
4846 const std::size_t element_type_parse_position = chars_read;
4847 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_bson_cstr(key))) {
4848 return false;
4849 }
4850
4851 if (not is_array and not sax->key(key)) {
4852 return false;
4853 }
4854
4855 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_internal(element_type, element_type_parse_position))) {
4856 return false;
4857 }
4858
4859 // get_bson_cstr only appends
4860 key.clear();
4861 }
4862
4863 return true;
4864 }
4865
4870 bool parse_bson_array() {
4871 std::int32_t document_size;
4872 get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
4873
4874 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1)))) {
4875 return false;
4876 }
4877
4878 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/ true))) {
4879 return false;
4880 }
4881
4882 return sax->end_array();
4883 }
4884
4886 // CBOR //
4888
4896 bool parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char = true) {
4897 switch (get_char ? get() : current) {
4898 // EOF
4899 case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
4900 return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "value");
4901
4902 // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
4903 case 0x00:
4904 case 0x01:
4905 case 0x02:
4906 case 0x03:
4907 case 0x04:
4908 case 0x05:
4909 case 0x06:
4910 case 0x07:
4911 case 0x08:
4912 case 0x09:
4913 case 0x0A:
4914 case 0x0B:
4915 case 0x0C:
4916 case 0x0D:
4917 case 0x0E:
4918 case 0x0F:
4919 case 0x10:
4920 case 0x11:
4921 case 0x12:
4922 case 0x13:
4923 case 0x14:
4924 case 0x15:
4925 case 0x16:
4926 case 0x17:
4927 return sax->number_unsigned(static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current));
4928
4929 case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
4930 {
4931 std::uint8_t number;
4932 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
4933 }
4934
4935 case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
4936 {
4937 std::uint16_t number;
4938 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
4939 }
4940
4941 case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
4942 {
4943 std::uint32_t number;
4944 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
4945 }
4946
4947 case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
4948 {
4949 std::uint64_t number;
4950 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
4951 }
4952
4953 // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
4954 case 0x20:
4955 case 0x21:
4956 case 0x22:
4957 case 0x23:
4958 case 0x24:
4959 case 0x25:
4960 case 0x26:
4961 case 0x27:
4962 case 0x28:
4963 case 0x29:
4964 case 0x2A:
4965 case 0x2B:
4966 case 0x2C:
4967 case 0x2D:
4968 case 0x2E:
4969 case 0x2F:
4970 case 0x30:
4971 case 0x31:
4972 case 0x32:
4973 case 0x33:
4974 case 0x34:
4975 case 0x35:
4976 case 0x36:
4977 case 0x37:
4978 return sax->number_integer(static_cast<std::int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current));
4979
4980 case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
4981 {
4982 std::uint8_t number;
4983 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and
4984 sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
4985 }
4986
4987 case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
4988 {
4989 std::uint16_t number;
4990 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and
4991 sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
4992 }
4993
4994 case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
4995 {
4996 std::uint32_t number;
4997 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and
4998 sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
4999 }
5000
5001 case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
5002 {
5003 std::uint64_t number;
5004 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and
5005 sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - static_cast<number_integer_t>(number));
5006 }
5007
5008 // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
5009 case 0x60:
5010 case 0x61:
5011 case 0x62:
5012 case 0x63:
5013 case 0x64:
5014 case 0x65:
5015 case 0x66:
5016 case 0x67:
5017 case 0x68:
5018 case 0x69:
5019 case 0x6A:
5020 case 0x6B:
5021 case 0x6C:
5022 case 0x6D:
5023 case 0x6E:
5024 case 0x6F:
5025 case 0x70:
5026 case 0x71:
5027 case 0x72:
5028 case 0x73:
5029 case 0x74:
5030 case 0x75:
5031 case 0x76:
5032 case 0x77:
5033 case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5034 case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5035 case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5036 case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5037 case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
5038 {
5039 string_t s;
5040 return get_cbor_string(s) and sax->string(s);
5041 }
5042
5043 // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
5044 case 0x80:
5045 case 0x81:
5046 case 0x82:
5047 case 0x83:
5048 case 0x84:
5049 case 0x85:
5050 case 0x86:
5051 case 0x87:
5052 case 0x88:
5053 case 0x89:
5054 case 0x8A:
5055 case 0x8B:
5056 case 0x8C:
5057 case 0x8D:
5058 case 0x8E:
5059 case 0x8F:
5060 case 0x90:
5061 case 0x91:
5062 case 0x92:
5063 case 0x93:
5064 case 0x94:
5065 case 0x95:
5066 case 0x96:
5067 case 0x97:
5068 return get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu));
5069
5070 case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5071 {
5072 std::uint8_t len;
5073 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5074 }
5075
5076 case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5077 {
5078 std::uint16_t len;
5079 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5080 }
5081
5082 case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5083 {
5084 std::uint32_t len;
5085 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5086 }
5087
5088 case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5089 {
5090 std::uint64_t len;
5091 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5092 }
5093
5094 case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
5095 return get_cbor_array(std::size_t(-1));
5096
5097 // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
5098 case 0xA0:
5099 case 0xA1:
5100 case 0xA2:
5101 case 0xA3:
5102 case 0xA4:
5103 case 0xA5:
5104 case 0xA6:
5105 case 0xA7:
5106 case 0xA8:
5107 case 0xA9:
5108 case 0xAA:
5109 case 0xAB:
5110 case 0xAC:
5111 case 0xAD:
5112 case 0xAE:
5113 case 0xAF:
5114 case 0xB0:
5115 case 0xB1:
5116 case 0xB2:
5117 case 0xB3:
5118 case 0xB4:
5119 case 0xB5:
5120 case 0xB6:
5121 case 0xB7:
5122 return get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu));
5123
5124 case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5125 {
5126 std::uint8_t len;
5127 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5128 }
5129
5130 case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5131 {
5132 std::uint16_t len;
5133 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5134 }
5135
5136 case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5137 {
5138 std::uint32_t len;
5139 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5140 }
5141
5142 case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5143 {
5144 std::uint64_t len;
5145 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5146 }
5147
5148 case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
5149 return get_cbor_object(std::size_t(-1));
5150
5151 case 0xF4: // false
5152 return sax->boolean(false);
5153
5154 case 0xF5: // true
5155 return sax->boolean(true);
5156
5157 case 0xF6: // null
5158 return sax->null();
5159
5160 case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
5161 {
5162 const int byte1_raw = get();
5163 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number"))) {
5164 return false;
5165 }
5166 const int byte2_raw = get();
5167 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number"))) {
5168 return false;
5169 }
5170
5171 const auto byte1 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte1_raw);
5172 const auto byte2 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte2_raw);
5173
5174 // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
5175 // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
5176 // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
5177 // still only have limited support for them. It is very
5178 // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
5179 // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
5180 // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
5181 // is shown in Fig. 3.
5182 const auto half = static_cast<unsigned int>((byte1 << 8u) + byte2);
5183 const double val = [&half] {
5184 const int exp = (half >> 10u) & 0x1Fu;
5185 const unsigned int mant = half & 0x3FFu;
5186 assert(0 <= exp and exp <= 32);
5187 assert(mant <= 1024);
5188 switch (exp) {
5189 case 0:
5190 return std::ldexp(mant, -24);
5191 case 31:
5192 return (mant == 0) ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
5193 : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
5194 default:
5195 return std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
5196 }
5197 }();
5198 return sax->number_float(
5199 (half & 0x8000u) != 0 ? static_cast<number_float_t>(-val) : static_cast<number_float_t>(val), "");
5200 }
5201
5202 case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
5203 {
5204 float number;
5205 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and
5206 sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5207 }
5208
5209 case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
5210 {
5211 double number;
5212 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and
5213 sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5214 }
5215
5216 default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
5217 {
5218 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5219 return sax->parse_error(
5220 chars_read, last_token,
5221 parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
5222 exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
5223 }
5224 }
5225 }
5226
5238 bool get_cbor_string(string_t& result) {
5239 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "string"))) {
5240 return false;
5241 }
5242
5243 switch (current) {
5244 // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
5245 case 0x60:
5246 case 0x61:
5247 case 0x62:
5248 case 0x63:
5249 case 0x64:
5250 case 0x65:
5251 case 0x66:
5252 case 0x67:
5253 case 0x68:
5254 case 0x69:
5255 case 0x6A:
5256 case 0x6B:
5257 case 0x6C:
5258 case 0x6D:
5259 case 0x6E:
5260 case 0x6F:
5261 case 0x70:
5262 case 0x71:
5263 case 0x72:
5264 case 0x73:
5265 case 0x74:
5266 case 0x75:
5267 case 0x76:
5268 case 0x77: {
5269 return get_string(input_format_t::cbor, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
5270 }
5271
5272 case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5273 {
5274 std::uint8_t len;
5275 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
5276 }
5277
5278 case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5279 {
5280 std::uint16_t len;
5281 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
5282 }
5283
5284 case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5285 {
5286 std::uint32_t len;
5287 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
5288 }
5289
5290 case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5291 {
5292 std::uint64_t len;
5293 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
5294 }
5295
5296 case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
5297 {
5298 while (get() != 0xFF) {
5299 string_t chunk;
5300 if (not get_cbor_string(chunk)) {
5301 return false;
5302 }
5303 result.append(chunk);
5304 }
5305 return true;
5306 }
5307
5308 default: {
5309 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5310 return sax->parse_error(
5311 chars_read, last_token,
5312 parse_error::create(
5313 113, chars_read,
5314 exception_message(
5315 input_format_t::cbor,
5316 "expected length specification (0x60-0x7B) or indefinite string type (0x7F); last byte: 0x" +
5317 last_token,
5318 "string")));
5319 }
5320 }
5321 }
5322
5328 bool get_cbor_array(const std::size_t len) {
5329 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len))) {
5330 return false;
5331 }
5332
5333 if (len != std::size_t(-1)) {
5334 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
5335 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal())) {
5336 return false;
5337 }
5338 }
5339 } else {
5340 while (get() != 0xFF) {
5341 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal(false))) {
5342 return false;
5343 }
5344 }
5345 }
5346
5347 return sax->end_array();
5348 }
5349
5355 bool get_cbor_object(const std::size_t len) {
5356 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(len))) {
5357 return false;
5358 }
5359
5360 string_t key;
5361 if (len != std::size_t(-1)) {
5362 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
5363 get();
5364 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key))) {
5365 return false;
5366 }
5367
5368 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal())) {
5369 return false;
5370 }
5371 key.clear();
5372 }
5373 } else {
5374 while (get() != 0xFF) {
5375 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key))) {
5376 return false;
5377 }
5378
5379 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal())) {
5380 return false;
5381 }
5382 key.clear();
5383 }
5384 }
5385
5386 return sax->end_object();
5387 }

5572 case 0xA0:
5573 case 0xA1:
5574 case 0xA2:
5575 case 0xA3:
5576 case 0xA4:
5577 case 0xA5:
5578 case 0xA6:
5579 case 0xA7:
5580 case 0xA8:
5581 case 0xA9:
5582 case 0xAA:
5583 case 0xAB:
5584 case 0xAC:
5585 case 0xAD:
5586 case 0xAE:
5587 case 0xAF:
5588 case 0xB0:
5589 case 0xB1:
5590 case 0xB2:
5591 case 0xB3:

5597 case 0xB9:

5599 case 0xBB:
5600 case 0xBC:
5601 case 0xBD:
5602 case 0xBE:
5603 case 0xBF:
5604 case 0xD9: // str 8
5605 case 0xDA: // str 16
5606 case 0xDB: // str 32
5607 {
5608 string_t s;
5609 return get_msgpack_string(s) and sax->string(s);
5610 }

5613 return sax->null();
5614
5615 case 0xC2: // false
5616 return sax->boolean(false);
5617
5618 case 0xC3: // true
5619 return sax->boolean(true);
5620
5621 case 0xCA: // float 32
5622 {
5623 float number;
5624 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and
5625 sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5626 }
5627
5628 case 0xCB: // float 64
5629 {
5630 double number;
5631 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and
5632 sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5633 }
5634
5635 case 0xCC: // uint 8
5636 {
5637 std::uint8_t number;
5638 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5639 }
5640
5641 case 0xCD: // uint 16
5642 {
5643 std::uint16_t number;
5644 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5645 }
5646
5647 case 0xCE: // uint 32
5648 {
5649 std::uint32_t number;
5650 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5651 }
5652
5653 case 0xCF: // uint 64
5654 {
5655 std::uint64_t number;
5656 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5657 }
5658
5659 case 0xD0: // int 8
5660 {
5661 std::int8_t number;
5662 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5663 }
5664
5665 case 0xD1: // int 16
5666 {
5667 std::int16_t number;
5668 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5669 }
5670
5671 case 0xD2: // int 32
5672 {
5673 std::int32_t number;
5674 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5675 }
5676
5677 case 0xD3: // int 64
5678 {
5679 std::int64_t number;
5680 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5681 }
5682
5683 case 0xDC: // array 16
5684 {
5685 std::uint16_t len;
5686 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_msgpack_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5687 }
5688
5689 case 0xDD: // array 32
5690 {
5691 std::uint32_t len;
5692 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_msgpack_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5693 }
5694
5695 case 0xDE: // map 16
5696 {
5697 std::uint16_t len;
5698 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_msgpack_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5699 }
5700
5701 case 0xDF: // map 32
5702 {
5703 std::uint32_t len;
5704 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_msgpack_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
5705 }
5706
5707 // negative fixint
5708 case 0xE0:
5709 case 0xE1:
5710 case 0xE2:
5711 case 0xE3:
5712 case 0xE4:
5713 case 0xE5:
5714 case 0xE6:
5715 case 0xE7:
5716 case 0xE8:
5717 case 0xE9:
5718 case 0xEA:
5719 case 0xEB:
5720 case 0xEC:
5721 case 0xED:
5722 case 0xEE:
5723 case 0xEF:
5724 case 0xF0:
5725 case 0xF1:
5726 case 0xF2:
5727 case 0xF3:
5728 case 0xF4:
5729 case 0xF5:
5730 case 0xF6:
5731 case 0xF7:
5732 case 0xF8:
5733 case 0xF9:
5734 case 0xFA:
5735 case 0xFB:
5736 case 0xFC:
5737 case 0xFD:
5738 case 0xFE:
5739 case 0xFF:
5740 return sax->number_integer(static_cast<std::int8_t>(current));
5741
5742 default: // anything else
5743 {
5744 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5745 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token,
5746 parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
5747 exception_message(input_format_t::msgpack,
5748 "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
5749 }
5750 }
5751 }
5752
5763 bool get_msgpack_string(string_t& result) {
5764 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::msgpack, "string"))) {
5765 return false;
5766 }
5767
5768 switch (current) {
5769 // fixstr
5770 case 0xA0:
5771 case 0xA1:
5772 case 0xA2:
5773 case 0xA3:
5774 case 0xA4:
5775 case 0xA5:
5776 case 0xA6:
5777 case 0xA7:
5778 case 0xA8:
5779 case 0xA9:
5780 case 0xAA:
5781 case 0xAB:
5782 case 0xAC:
5783 case 0xAD:
5784 case 0xAE:
5785 case 0xAF:
5786 case 0xB0:
5787 case 0xB1:
5788 case 0xB2:
5789 case 0xB3:
5790 case 0xB4:
5791 case 0xB5:
5792 case 0xB6:
5793 case 0xB7:
5794 case 0xB8:
5795 case 0xB9:
5796 case 0xBA:
5797 case 0xBB:
5798 case 0xBC:
5799 case 0xBD:
5800 case 0xBE:
5801 case 0xBF: {
5802 return get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
5803 }
5804
5805 case 0xD9: // str 8
5806 {
5807 std::uint8_t len;
5808 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
5809 }
5810
5811 case 0xDA: // str 16
5812 {
5813 std::uint16_t len;
5814 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
5815 }
5816
5817 case 0xDB: // str 32
5818 {
5819 std::uint32_t len;
5820 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
5821 }
5822
5823 default: {
5824 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5825 return sax->parse_error(
5826 chars_read, last_token,
5827 parse_error::create(
5828 113, chars_read,
5829 exception_message(
5830 input_format_t::msgpack,
5831 "expected length specification (0xA0-0xBF, 0xD9-0xDB); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
5832 }
5833 }
5834 }
5835
5840 bool get_msgpack_array(const std::size_t len) {
5841 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len))) {
5842 return false;
5843 }
5844
5845 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
5846 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal())) {
5847 return false;
5848 }
5849 }
5850
5851 return sax->end_array();
5852 }
5853
5858 bool get_msgpack_object(const std::size_t len) {
5859 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(len))) {
5860 return false;
5861 }
5862
5863 string_t key;
5864 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
5865 get();
5866 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_msgpack_string(key) or not sax->key(key))) {
5867 return false;
5868 }
5869
5870 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal())) {
5871 return false;
5872 }
5873 key.clear();
5874 }
5875
5876 return sax->end_object();
5877 }
5878
5880 // UBJSON //
5882
5890 bool parse_ubjson_internal(const bool get_char = true) {
5891 return get_ubjson_value(get_char ? get_ignore_noop() : current);
5892 }
5893
5908 bool get_ubjson_string(string_t& result, const bool get_char = true) {
5909 if (get_char) {
5910 get(); // TODO(niels): may we ignore N here?
5911 }
5912
5913 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value"))) {
5914 return false;
5915 }
5916
5917 switch (current) {
5918 case 'U': {
5919 std::uint8_t len;
5920 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
5921 }
5922
5923 case 'i': {
5924 std::int8_t len;
5925 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
5926 }
5927
5928 case 'I': {
5929 std::int16_t len;
5930 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
5931 }
5932
5933 case 'l': {
5934 std::int32_t len;
5935 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
5936 }
5937
5938 case 'L': {
5939 std::int64_t len;
5940 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
5941 }
5942
5943 default:
5944 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5945 return sax->parse_error(
5946 chars_read, last_token,
5947 parse_error::create(
5948 113, chars_read,
5949 exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson,
5950 "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L); last byte: 0x" + last_token,
5951 "string")));
5952 }
5953 }
5954
5959 bool get_ubjson_size_value(std::size_t& result) {
5960 switch (get_ignore_noop()) {
5961 case 'U': {
5962 std::uint8_t number;
5963 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number))) {
5964 return false;
5965 }
5966 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5967 return true;
5968 }
5969
5970 case 'i': {
5971 std::int8_t number;
5972 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number))) {
5973 return false;
5974 }
5975 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5976 return true;
5977 }
5978
5979 case 'I': {
5980 std::int16_t number;
5981 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number))) {
5982 return false;
5983 }
5984 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5985 return true;
5986 }
5987
5988 case 'l': {
5989 std::int32_t number;
5990 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number))) {
5991 return false;
5992 }
5993 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5994 return true;
5995 }
5996
5997 case 'L': {
5998 std::int64_t number;
5999 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number))) {
6000 return false;
6001 }
6002 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
6003 return true;
6004 }
6005
6006 default: {
6007 auto last_token = get_token_string();
6008 return sax->parse_error(
6009 chars_read, last_token,
6010 parse_error::create(
6011 113, chars_read,
6012 exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson,
6013 "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L) after '#'; last byte: 0x" +
6014 last_token,
6015 "size")));
6016 }
6017 }
6018 }
6019
6030 bool get_ubjson_size_type(std::pair<std::size_t, int>& result) {
6031 result.first = string_t::npos; // size
6032 result.second = 0; // type
6033
6034 get_ignore_noop();
6035
6036 if (current == '$') {
6037 result.second = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
6038 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "type"))) {
6039 return false;
6040 }
6041
6042 get_ignore_noop();
6043 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current != '#')) {
6044 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value"))) {
6045 return false;
6046 }
6047 auto last_token = get_token_string();
6048 return sax->parse_error(
6049 chars_read, last_token,
6050 parse_error::create(
6051 112, chars_read,
6052 exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson,
6053 "expected '#' after type information; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "size")));
6054 }
6055
6056 return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
6057 }
6058
6059 if (current == '#') {
6060 return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
6061 }
6062
6063 return true;
6064 }
6065
6070 bool get_ubjson_value(const int prefix) {
6071 switch (prefix) {
6072 case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): // EOF
6073 return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value");
6074
6075 case 'T': // true
6076 return sax->boolean(true);
6077 case 'F': // false
6078 return sax->boolean(false);
6079
6080 case 'Z': // null
6081 return sax->null();
6082
6083 case 'U': {
6084 std::uint8_t number;
6085 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
6086 }
6087
6088 case 'i': {
6089 std::int8_t number;
6090 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
6091 }
6092
6093 case 'I': {
6094 std::int16_t number;
6095 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
6096 }
6097
6098 case 'l': {
6099 std::int32_t number;
6100 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
6101 }
6102
6103 case 'L': {
6104 std::int64_t number;
6105 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
6106 }
6107
6108 case 'd': {
6109 float number;
6110 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and
6111 sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
6112 }
6113
6114 case 'D': {
6115 double number;
6116 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and
6117 sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
6118 }
6119
6120 case 'C': // char
6121 {
6122 get();
6123 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "char"))) {
6124 return false;
6125 }
6126 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current > 127)) {
6127 auto last_token = get_token_string();
6128 return sax->parse_error(
6129 chars_read, last_token,
6130 parse_error::create(
6131 113, chars_read,
6132 exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson,
6133 "byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x" + last_token,
6134 "char")));
6135 }
6136 string_t s(1, static_cast<char>(current));
6137 return sax->string(s);
6138 }
6139
6140 case 'S': // string
6141 {
6142 string_t s;
6143 return get_ubjson_string(s) and sax->string(s);
6144 }
6145
6146 case '[': // array
6147 return get_ubjson_array();
6148
6149 case '{': // object
6150 return get_ubjson_object();
6151
6152 default: // anything else
6153 {
6154 auto last_token = get_token_string();
6155 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token,
6156 parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
6157 exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson,
6158 "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
6159 }
6160 }
6161 }
6162
6166 bool get_ubjson_array() {
6167 std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
6168 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type))) {
6169 return false;
6170 }
6171
6172 if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos) {
6173 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(size_and_type.first))) {
6174 return false;
6175 }
6176
6177 if (size_and_type.second != 0) {
6178 if (size_and_type.second != 'N') {
6179 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i) {
6180 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second))) {
6181 return false;
6182 }
6183 }
6184 }
6185 } else {
6186 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i) {
6187 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal())) {
6188 return false;
6189 }
6190 }
6191 }
6192 } else {
6193 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1)))) {
6194 return false;
6195 }
6196
6197 while (current != ']') {
6198 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal(false))) {
6199 return false;
6200 }
6201 get_ignore_noop();
6202 }
6203 }
6204
6205 return sax->end_array();
6206 }
6207
6211 bool get_ubjson_object() {
6212 std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
6213 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type))) {
6214 return false;
6215 }
6216
6217 string_t key;
6218 if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos) {
6219 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(size_and_type.first))) {
6220 return false;
6221 }
6222
6223 if (size_and_type.second != 0) {
6224 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i) {
6225 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key))) {
6226 return false;
6227 }
6228 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second))) {
6229 return false;
6230 }
6231 key.clear();
6232 }
6233 } else {
6234 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i) {
6235 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key))) {
6236 return false;
6237 }
6238 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal())) {
6239 return false;
6240 }
6241 key.clear();
6242 }
6243 }
6244 } else {
6245 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1)))) {
6246 return false;
6247 }
6248
6249 while (current != '}') {
6250 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key, false) or not sax->key(key))) {
6251 return false;
6252 }
6253 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal())) {
6254 return false;
6255 }
6256 get_ignore_noop();
6257 key.clear();
6258 }
6259 }
6260
6261 return sax->end_object();
6262 }
6263
6265 // Utility functions //
6267
6277 int get() {
6278 ++chars_read;
6279 return current = ia->get_character();
6280 }
6281
6285 int get_ignore_noop() {
6286 do {
6287 get();
6288 } while (current == 'N');
6289
6290 return current;
6291 }
6292
6293 /*
6294 @brief read a number from the input
6295
6296 @tparam NumberType the type of the number
6297 @param[in] format the current format (for diagnostics)
6298 @param[out] result number of type @a NumberType
6299
6300 @return whether conversion completed
6301
6302 @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
6303 bytes in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order
6304 (big endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
6305 */
6306 template <typename NumberType, bool InputIsLittleEndian = false>
6307 bool get_number(const input_format_t format, NumberType& result) {
6308 // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
6309 std::array<std::uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
6310 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i) {
6311 get();
6312 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(format, "number"))) {
6313 return false;
6314 }
6315
6316 // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
6317 if (is_little_endian != InputIsLittleEndian) {
6318 vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current);
6319 } else {
6320 vec[i] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6321 }
6322 }
6323
6324 // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
6325 std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
6326 return true;
6327 }
6328
6343 template <typename NumberType>
6344 bool get_string(const input_format_t format, const NumberType len, string_t& result) {
6345 bool success = true;
6346 std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(result), len, [this, &success, &format]() {
6347 get();
6348 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(format, "string"))) {
6349 success = false;
6350 }
6351 return static_cast<char>(current);
6352 });
6353 return success;
6354 }
6355
6361 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
6362 bool unexpect_eof(const input_format_t format, const char* context) const {
6363 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
6364 return sax->parse_error(
6365 chars_read, "<end of file>",
6366 parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "unexpected end of input", context)));
6367 }
6368 return true;
6369 }
6370
6374 std::string get_token_string() const {
6375 std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
6376 (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(current));
6377 return std::string{cr.data()};
6378 }
6379
6386 std::string exception_message(const input_format_t format, const std::string& detail,
6387 const std::string& context) const {
6388 std::string error_msg = "syntax error while parsing ";
6389
6390 switch (format) {
6391 case input_format_t::cbor:
6392 error_msg += "CBOR";
6393 break;
6394
6395 case input_format_t::msgpack:
6396 error_msg += "MessagePack";
6397 break;
6398
6399 case input_format_t::ubjson:
6400 error_msg += "UBJSON";
6401 break;
6402
6403 case input_format_t::bson:
6404 error_msg += "BSON";
6405 break;
6406
6407 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6408 assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6409 }
6410
6411 return error_msg + " " + context + ": " + detail;
6412 }
6413
6414private:
6416 input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
6417
6419 int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
6420
6422 std::size_t chars_read = 0;
6423
6425 const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
6426
6428 json_sax_t* sax = nullptr;
6429};
6430} // namespace detail
6431} // namespace nlohmann

6456// lexer //
6458
6464template <typename BasicJsonType>
6465class lexer {
6466 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
6467 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
6468 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
6469 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
6470
6471public:
6473 enum class token_type {
6474 uninitialized,
6475 literal_true,
6476 literal_false,
6477 literal_null,
6478 value_string,
6479 value_unsigned,
6480 value_integer,
6481 value_float,
6482 begin_array,
6483 begin_object,
6484 end_array,
6485 end_object,
6486 name_separator,
6487 value_separator,
6488 parse_error,
6489 end_of_input,
6490 literal_or_value
6491 };
6492
6494 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
6495 JSON_HEDLEY_CONST
6496 static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept {
6497 switch (t) {
6498 case token_type::uninitialized:
6499 return "<uninitialized>";
6500 case token_type::literal_true:
6501 return "true literal";
6502 case token_type::literal_false:
6503 return "false literal";
6504 case token_type::literal_null:
6505 return "null literal";
6506 case token_type::value_string:
6507 return "string literal";
6508 case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
6509 case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
6510 case lexer::token_type::value_float:
6511 return "number literal";
6512 case token_type::begin_array:
6513 return "'['";
6514 case token_type::begin_object:
6515 return "'{'";
6516 case token_type::end_array:
6517 return "']'";
6518 case token_type::end_object:
6519 return "'}'";
6520 case token_type::name_separator:
6521 return "':'";
6522 case token_type::value_separator:
6523 return "','";
6524 case token_type::parse_error:
6525 return "<parse error>";
6526 case token_type::end_of_input:
6527 return "end of input";
6528 case token_type::literal_or_value:
6529 return "'[', '{', or a literal";
6530 // LCOV_EXCL_START
6531 default: // catch non-enum values
6532 return "unknown token";
6533 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6534 }
6535 }
6536
6537 explicit lexer(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter)
6538 : ia(std::move(adapter)), decimal_point_char(get_decimal_point()) {}

6542 lexer(lexer&&) = delete;
6543 lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
6544 lexer& operator=(lexer&&) = delete;
6545 ~lexer() = default;

6547private:
6549 // locales
6551
6553 JSON_HEDLEY_PURE
6554 static char get_decimal_point() noexcept {
6555 const auto loc = localeconv();
6556 assert(loc != nullptr);
6557 return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
6558 }
6559
6561 // scan functions
6563
6579 int get_codepoint() {
6580 // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
6581 assert(current == 'u');
6582 int codepoint = 0;
6583
6584 const auto factors = {12u, 8u, 4u, 0u};
6585 for (const auto factor : factors) {
6586 get();
6587
6588 if (current >= '0' and current <= '9') {
6589 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x30u) << factor);
6590 } else if (current >= 'A' and current <= 'F') {
6591 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x37u) << factor);
6592 } else if (current >= 'a' and current <= 'f') {
6593 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x57u) << factor);
6594 } else {
6595 return -1;
6596 }
6597 }
6598
6599 assert(0x0000 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
6600 return codepoint;
6601 }
6602
6618 bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<int> ranges) {
6619 assert(ranges.size() == 2 or ranges.size() == 4 or ranges.size() == 6);
6620 add(current);
6621
6622 for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range) {
6623 get();
6624 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(*range <= current and current <= *(++range))) {
6625 add(current);
6626 } else {
6627 error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
6628 return false;
6629 }
6630 }
6631
6632 return true;
6633 }
6634
6650 token_type scan_string() {
6651 // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
6652 reset();
6653
6654 // we entered the function by reading an open quote
6655 assert(current == '\"');
6656
6657 while (true) {
6658 // get next character
6659 switch (get()) {
6660 // end of file while parsing string
6661 case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): {
6662 error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
6663 return token_type::parse_error;
6664 }
6665
6666 // closing quote
6667 case '\"': {
6668 return token_type::value_string;
6669 }
6670
6671 // escapes
6672 case '\\': {
6673 switch (get()) {
6674 // quotation mark
6675 case '\"':
6676 add('\"');
6677 break;
6678 // reverse solidus
6679 case '\\':
6680 add('\\');
6681 break;
6682 // solidus
6683 case '/':
6684 add('/');
6685 break;
6686 // backspace
6687 case 'b':
6688 add('\b');
6689 break;
6690 // form feed
6691 case 'f':
6692 add('\f');
6693 break;
6694 // line feed
6695 case 'n':
6696 add('\n');
6697 break;
6698 // carriage return
6699 case 'r':
6700 add('\r');
6701 break;
6702 // tab
6703 case 't':
6704 add('\t');
6705 break;
6706
6707 // unicode escapes
6708 case 'u': {
6709 const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
6710 int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
6711
6712 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1)) {
6713 error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
6714 return token_type::parse_error;
6715 }
6716
6717 // check if code point is a high surrogate
6718 if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF) {
6719 // expect next \uxxxx entry
6720 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u')) {
6721 const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
6722
6723 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1)) {
6724 error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
6725 return token_type::parse_error;
6726 }
6727
6728 // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
6729 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF)) {
6730 // overwrite codepoint
6731 codepoint = static_cast<int>(
6732 // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
6733 (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint1) << 10u)
6734 // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
6735 + static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint2)
6736 // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
6737 // in the result so we have to subtract with:
6738 // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
6739 - 0x35FDC00u);
6740 } else {
6741 error_message =
6742 "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
6743 return token_type::parse_error;
6744 }
6745 } else {
6746 error_message =
6747 "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
6748 return token_type::parse_error;
6749 }
6750 } else {
6751 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF)) {
6752 error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
6753 return token_type::parse_error;
6754 }
6755 }
6756
6757 // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
6758 assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
6759
6760 // translate codepoint into bytes
6761 if (codepoint < 0x80) {
6762 // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
6763 add(codepoint);
6764 } else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF) {
6765 // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
6766 add(static_cast<int>(0xC0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u)));
6767 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
6768 } else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF) {
6769 // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
6770 add(static_cast<int>(0xE0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u)));
6771 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
6772 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
6773 } else {
6774 // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
6775 add(static_cast<int>(0xF0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 18u)));
6776 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u) & 0x3Fu)));
6777 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
6778 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
6779 }
6780
6781 break;
6782 }
6783
6784 // other characters after escape
6785 default:
6786 error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
6787 return token_type::parse_error;
6788 }
6789
6790 break;
6791 }
6792
6793 // invalid control characters
6794 case 0x00: {
6795 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0000 (NUL) must be escaped to \\u0000";
6796 return token_type::parse_error;
6797 }
6798
6799 case 0x01: {
6800 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0001 (SOH) must be escaped to \\u0001";
6801 return token_type::parse_error;
6802 }
6803
6804 case 0x02: {
6805 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0002 (STX) must be escaped to \\u0002";
6806 return token_type::parse_error;
6807 }
6808
6809 case 0x03: {
6810 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0003 (ETX) must be escaped to \\u0003";
6811 return token_type::parse_error;
6812 }
6813
6814 case 0x04: {
6815 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0004 (EOT) must be escaped to \\u0004";
6816 return token_type::parse_error;
6817 }
6818
6819 case 0x05: {
6820 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0005 (ENQ) must be escaped to \\u0005";
6821 return token_type::parse_error;
6822 }
6823
6824 case 0x06: {
6825 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0006 (ACK) must be escaped to \\u0006";
6826 return token_type::parse_error;
6827 }
6828
6829 case 0x07: {
6830 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0007 (BEL) must be escaped to \\u0007";
6831 return token_type::parse_error;
6832 }
6833
6834 case 0x08: {
6835 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0008 (BS) must be escaped to \\u0008 or \\b";
6836 return token_type::parse_error;
6837 }
6838
6839 case 0x09: {
6840 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0009 (HT) must be escaped to \\u0009 or \\t";
6841 return token_type::parse_error;
6842 }
6843
6844 case 0x0A: {
6845 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+000A (LF) must be escaped to \\u000A or \\n";
6846 return token_type::parse_error;
6847 }
6848
6849 case 0x0B: {
6850 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+000B (VT) must be escaped to \\u000B";
6851 return token_type::parse_error;
6852 }
6853
6854 case 0x0C: {
6855 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+000C (FF) must be escaped to \\u000C or \\f";
6856 return token_type::parse_error;
6857 }
6858
6859 case 0x0D: {
6860 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+000D (CR) must be escaped to \\u000D or \\r";
6861 return token_type::parse_error;
6862 }
6863

6986 case 0x40:
6987 case 0x41:
6988 case 0x42:
6989 case 0x43:
6990 case 0x44:
6991 case 0x45:
6992 case 0x46:
6993 case 0x47:
6994 case 0x48:
6995 case 0x49:
6996 case 0x4A:
6997 case 0x4B:
6998 case 0x4C:
6999 case 0x4D:
7000 case 0x4E:
7001 case 0x4F:
7002 case 0x50:
7003 case 0x51:
7004 case 0x52:
7005 case 0x53:
7006 case 0x54:
7007 case 0x55:
7008 case 0x56:
7009 case 0x57:
7010 case 0x58:
7011 case 0x59:
7012 case 0x5A:
7013 case 0x5B:
7014 case 0x5D:
7015 case 0x5E:
7016 case 0x5F:
7017 case 0x60:
7018 case 0x61:
7019 case 0x62:
7020 case 0x63:
7021 case 0x64:
7022 case 0x65:
7023 case 0x66:
7024 case 0x67:
7025 case 0x68:
7026 case 0x69:
7027 case 0x6A:
7028 case 0x6B:
7029 case 0x6C:
7030 case 0x6D:
7031 case 0x6E:
7032 case 0x6F:
7033 case 0x70:
7034 case 0x71:
7035 case 0x72:
7036 case 0x73:
7037 case 0x74:
7038 case 0x75:
7039 case 0x76:
7040 case 0x77:
7041 case 0x78:
7042 case 0x79:
7043 case 0x7A:
7044 case 0x7B:
7045 case 0x7C:
7046 case 0x7D:
7047 case 0x7E:
7048 case 0x7F: {
7049 add(current);
7050 break;
7051 }
7052
7053 // U+0080..U+07FF: bytes C2..DF 80..BF
7054 case 0xC2:
7055 case 0xC3:
7056 case 0xC4:
7057 case 0xC5:
7058 case 0xC6:
7059 case 0xC7:
7060 case 0xC8:
7061 case 0xC9:
7062 case 0xCA:
7063 case 0xCB:
7064 case 0xCC:
7065 case 0xCD:
7066 case 0xCE:
7067 case 0xCF:
7068 case 0xD0:
7069 case 0xD1:
7070 case 0xD2:
7071 case 0xD3:
7072 case 0xD4:
7073 case 0xD5:
7074 case 0xD6:
7075 case 0xD7:
7076 case 0xD8:
7077 case 0xD9:
7078 case 0xDA:
7079 case 0xDB:
7080 case 0xDC:
7081 case 0xDD:
7082 case 0xDE:
7083 case 0xDF: {
7084 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF}))) {
7085 return token_type::parse_error;
7086 }
7087 break;
7088 }
7089
7090 // U+0800..U+0FFF: bytes E0 A0..BF 80..BF
7091 case 0xE0: {
7092 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0xA0, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
7093 return token_type::parse_error;
7094 }
7095 break;
7096 }
7097
7098 // U+1000..U+CFFF: bytes E1..EC 80..BF 80..BF
7099 // U+E000..U+FFFF: bytes EE..EF 80..BF 80..BF
7100 case 0xE1:
7101 case 0xE2:
7102 case 0xE3:
7103 case 0xE4:
7104 case 0xE5:
7105 case 0xE6:
7106 case 0xE7:
7107 case 0xE8:
7108 case 0xE9:
7109 case 0xEA:
7110 case 0xEB:
7111 case 0xEC:
7112 case 0xEE:
7113 case 0xEF: {
7114 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
7115 return token_type::parse_error;
7116 }
7117 break;
7118 }
7119
7120 // U+D000..U+D7FF: bytes ED 80..9F 80..BF
7121 case 0xED: {
7122 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x9F, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
7123 return token_type::parse_error;
7124 }
7125 break;
7126 }
7127
7128 // U+10000..U+3FFFF F0 90..BF 80..BF 80..BF
7129 case 0xF0: {
7130 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x90, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
7131 return token_type::parse_error;
7132 }
7133 break;
7134 }
7135
7136 // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
7137 case 0xF1:
7138 case 0xF2:
7139 case 0xF3: {
7140 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
7141 return token_type::parse_error;
7142 }
7143 break;
7144 }
7145
7146 // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
7147 case 0xF4: {
7148 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x8F, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
7149 return token_type::parse_error;
7150 }
7151 break;
7152 }
7153
7154 // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
7155 default: {
7156 error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
7157 return token_type::parse_error;
7158 }
7159 }
7160 }
7161 }
7162
7163 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7164 static void strtof(float& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept { f = std::strtof(str, endptr); }
7165
7166 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7167 static void strtof(double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept { f = std::strtod(str, endptr); }
7168
7169 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7170 static void strtof(long double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept { f = std::strtold(str, endptr); }
7171
7212 token_type scan_number() // lgtm [cpp/use-of-goto]
7213 {
7214 // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
7215 reset();
7216
7217 // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
7218 // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
7219 token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
7220
7221 // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
7222 switch (current) {
7223 case '-': {
7224 add(current);
7225 goto scan_number_minus;
7226 }
7227
7228 case '0': {
7229 add(current);
7230 goto scan_number_zero;
7231 }
7232
7233 case '1':
7234 case '2':
7235 case '3':
7236 case '4':
7237 case '5':
7238 case '6':
7239 case '7':
7240 case '8':
7241 case '9': {
7242 add(current);
7243 goto scan_number_any1;
7244 }
7245
7246 // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
7247 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
7248 assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
7249 }
7250
7251 scan_number_minus:
7252 // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
7253 number_type = token_type::value_integer;
7254 switch (get()) {
7255 case '0': {
7256 add(current);
7257 goto scan_number_zero;
7258 }
7259
7260 case '1':
7261 case '2':
7262 case '3':
7263 case '4':
7264 case '5':
7265 case '6':
7266 case '7':
7267 case '8':
7268 case '9': {
7269 add(current);
7270 goto scan_number_any1;
7271 }
7272
7273 default: {
7274 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
7275 return token_type::parse_error;
7276 }
7277 }
7278
7279 scan_number_zero:
7280 // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
7281 switch (get()) {
7282 case '.': {
7283 add(decimal_point_char);
7284 goto scan_number_decimal1;
7285 }
7286
7287 case 'e':
7288 case 'E': {
7289 add(current);
7290 goto scan_number_exponent;
7291 }
7292
7293 default:
7294 goto scan_number_done;
7295 }
7296
7297 scan_number_any1:
7298 // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
7299 switch (get()) {
7300 case '0':
7301 case '1':
7302 case '2':
7303 case '3':
7304 case '4':
7305 case '5':
7306 case '6':
7307 case '7':
7308 case '8':
7309 case '9': {
7310 add(current);
7311 goto scan_number_any1;
7312 }
7313
7314 case '.': {
7315 add(decimal_point_char);
7316 goto scan_number_decimal1;
7317 }
7318
7319 case 'e':
7320 case 'E': {
7321 add(current);
7322 goto scan_number_exponent;
7323 }
7324
7325 default:
7326 goto scan_number_done;
7327 }
7328
7329 scan_number_decimal1:
7330 // state: we just parsed a decimal point
7331 number_type = token_type::value_float;
7332 switch (get()) {
7333 case '0':
7334 case '1':
7335 case '2':
7336 case '3':
7337 case '4':
7338 case '5':
7339 case '6':
7340 case '7':
7341 case '8':
7342 case '9': {
7343 add(current);
7344 goto scan_number_decimal2;
7345 }
7346
7347 default: {
7348 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
7349 return token_type::parse_error;
7350 }
7351 }
7352
7353 scan_number_decimal2:
7354 // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
7355 switch (get()) {
7356 case '0':
7357 case '1':
7358 case '2':
7359 case '3':
7360 case '4':
7361 case '5':
7362 case '6':
7363 case '7':
7364 case '8':
7365 case '9': {
7366 add(current);
7367 goto scan_number_decimal2;
7368 }
7369
7370 case 'e':
7371 case 'E': {
7372 add(current);
7373 goto scan_number_exponent;
7374 }
7375
7376 default:
7377 goto scan_number_done;
7378 }
7379
7380 scan_number_exponent:
7381 // we just parsed an exponent
7382 number_type = token_type::value_float;
7383 switch (get()) {
7384 case '+':
7385 case '-': {
7386 add(current);
7387 goto scan_number_sign;
7388 }
7389
7390 case '0':
7391 case '1':
7392 case '2':
7393 case '3':
7394 case '4':
7395 case '5':
7396 case '6':
7397 case '7':
7398 case '8':
7399 case '9': {
7400 add(current);
7401 goto scan_number_any2;
7402 }
7403
7404 default: {
7405 error_message = "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
7406 return token_type::parse_error;
7407 }
7408 }
7409
7410 scan_number_sign:
7411 // we just parsed an exponent sign
7412 switch (get()) {
7413 case '0':
7414 case '1':
7415 case '2':
7416 case '3':
7417 case '4':
7418 case '5':
7419 case '6':
7420 case '7':
7421 case '8':
7422 case '9': {
7423 add(current);
7424 goto scan_number_any2;
7425 }
7426
7427 default: {
7428 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
7429 return token_type::parse_error;
7430 }
7431 }
7432
7433 scan_number_any2:
7434 // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
7435 switch (get()) {
7436 case '0':
7437 case '1':
7438 case '2':
7439 case '3':
7440 case '4':
7441 case '5':
7442 case '6':
7443 case '7':
7444 case '8':
7445 case '9': {
7446 add(current);
7447 goto scan_number_any2;
7448 }
7449
7450 default:
7451 goto scan_number_done;
7452 }
7453
7454 scan_number_done:
7455 // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
7456 // we are done scanning a number)
7457 unget();
7458
7459 char* endptr = nullptr;
7460 errno = 0;
7461
7462 // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
7463 if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned) {
7464 const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
7465
7466 // we checked the number format before
7467 assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7468
7469 if (errno == 0) {
7470 value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
7471 if (value_unsigned == x) {
7472 return token_type::value_unsigned;
7473 }
7474 }
7475 } else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer) {
7476 const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
7477
7478 // we checked the number format before
7479 assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7480
7481 if (errno == 0) {
7482 value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
7483 if (value_integer == x) {
7484 return token_type::value_integer;
7485 }
7486 }
7487 }
7488
7489 // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
7490 // integer conversion above failed
7491 strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
7492
7493 // we checked the number format before
7494 assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7495
7496 return token_type::value_float;
7497 }
7498
7504 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7505 token_type scan_literal(const char* literal_text, const std::size_t length, token_type return_type) {
7506 assert(current == literal_text[0]);
7507 for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i) {
7508 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get() != literal_text[i])) {
7509 error_message = "invalid literal";
7510 return token_type::parse_error;
7511 }
7512 }
7513 return return_type;
7514 }
7515
7517 // input management
7519
7521 void reset() noexcept {
7522 token_buffer.clear();
7523 token_string.clear();
7524 token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
7525 }
7526
7527 /*
7528 @brief get next character from the input
7529
7530 This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
7531 not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
7532 `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
7533 for use in error messages.
7534
7535 @return character read from the input
7536 */
7537 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get() {
7538 ++position.chars_read_total;
7539 ++position.chars_read_current_line;
7540
7541 if (next_unget) {
7542 // just reset the next_unget variable and work with current
7543 next_unget = false;
7544 } else {
7545 current = ia->get_character();
7546 }
7547
7548 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
7549 token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
7550 }
7551
7552 if (current == '\n') {
7553 ++position.lines_read;
7554 position.chars_read_current_line = 0;
7555 }
7556
7557 return current;
7558 }
7559
7568 void unget() {
7569 next_unget = true;
7570
7571 --position.chars_read_total;
7572
7573 // in case we "unget" a newline, we have to also decrement the lines_read
7574 if (position.chars_read_current_line == 0) {
7575 if (position.lines_read > 0) {
7576 --position.lines_read;
7577 }
7578 } else {
7579 --position.chars_read_current_line;
7580 }
7581
7582 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
7583 assert(not token_string.empty());
7584 token_string.pop_back();
7585 }
7586 }
7587
7589 void add(int c) { token_buffer.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(c)); }
7590
7591public:
7593 // value getters
7595
7597 constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept { return value_integer; }
7598
7600 constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept { return value_unsigned; }
7601
7603 constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept { return value_float; }
7604
7606 string_t& get_string() { return token_buffer; }
7607
7609 // diagnostics
7611
7613 constexpr position_t get_position() const noexcept { return position; }
7614
7618 std::string get_token_string() const {
7619 // escape control characters
7620 std::string result;
7621 for (const auto c : token_string) {
7622 if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1F') {
7623 // escape control characters
7624 std::array<char, 9> cs{{}};
7625 (std::snprintf)(cs.data(), cs.size(), "<U+%.4X>", static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
7626 result += cs.data();
7627 } else {
7628 // add character as is
7629 result.push_back(c);
7630 }
7631 }
7632
7633 return result;
7634 }
7635
7637 JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
7638 constexpr const char* get_error_message() const noexcept { return error_message; }
7639
7641 // actual scanner
7643
7648 bool skip_bom() {
7649 if (get() == 0xEF) {
7650 // check if we completely parse the BOM
7651 return get() == 0xBB and get() == 0xBF;
7652 }
7653
7654 // the first character is not the beginning of the BOM; unget it to
7655 // process is later
7656 unget();
7657 return true;
7658 }
7659
7660 token_type scan() {
7661 // initially, skip the BOM
7662 if (position.chars_read_total == 0 and not skip_bom()) {
7663 error_message = "invalid BOM; must be 0xEF 0xBB 0xBF if given";
7664 return token_type::parse_error;
7665 }
7666
7667 // read next character and ignore whitespace
7668 do {
7669 get();
7670 } while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
7671
7672 switch (current) {
7673 // structural characters
7674 case '[':
7675 return token_type::begin_array;
7676 case ']':
7677 return token_type::end_array;
7678 case '{':
7679 return token_type::begin_object;
7680 case '}':
7681 return token_type::end_object;
7682 case ':':
7683 return token_type::name_separator;
7684 case ',':
7685 return token_type::value_separator;
7686
7687 // literals
7688 case 't':
7689 return scan_literal("true", 4, token_type::literal_true);
7690 case 'f':
7691 return scan_literal("false", 5, token_type::literal_false);
7692 case 'n':
7693 return scan_literal("null", 4, token_type::literal_null);
7694
7695 // string
7696 case '\"':
7697 return scan_string();
7698
7699 // number
7700 case '-':
7701 case '0':
7702 case '1':
7703 case '2':
7704 case '3':
7705 case '4':
7706 case '5':
7707 case '6':
7708 case '7':
7709 case '8':
7710 case '9':
7711 return scan_number();
7712
7713 // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
7714 // string literals)
7715 case '\0':
7716 case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
7717 return token_type::end_of_input;
7718
7719 // error
7720 default:
7721 error_message = "invalid literal";
7722 return token_type::parse_error;
7723 }
7724 }
7725
7726private:
7728 detail::input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
7729
7731 std::char_traits<char>::int_type current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
7732
7734 bool next_unget = false;
7735
7737 position_t position{};
7738
7740 std::vector<char> token_string{};
7741
7743 string_t token_buffer{};
7744
7746 const char* error_message = "";
7747
7748 // number values
7749 number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
7750 number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
7751 number_float_t value_float = 0;
7752
7754 const char decimal_point_char = '.';
7755};
7756} // namespace detail
7757} // namespace nlohmann

7771// #include <nlohmann/detail/input/input_adapters.hpp>
