7773// #include <nlohmann/detail/input/json_sax.hpp>
7774
7775// #include <nlohmann/detail/input/lexer.hpp>
7776
7777// #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
7778
7779// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/is_sax.hpp>
7780
7781// #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
7782
7783namespace nlohmann {
7784namespace detail {
7786// parser //
7788
7794template <typename BasicJsonType>
7795class parser {
7796 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
7797 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
7798 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
7799 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
7800 using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType>;
7801 using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
7802
7803public:
7804 enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t {
7806 object_start,
7808 object_end,
7810 array_start,
7812 array_end,
7814 key,
7816 value
7817 };
7818
7819 using parser_callback_t = std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType& parsed)>;
7820
7822 explicit parser(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter, const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr,
7823 const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
7824 : callback(cb), m_lexer(std::move(adapter)), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_) {
7825 // read first token
7826 get_token();
7827 }
7828
7839 void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result) {
7840 if (callback) {
7841 json_sax_dom_callback_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, callback, allow_exceptions);
7842 sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
7843 result.assert_invariant();
7844
7845 // in strict mode, input must be completely read
7846 if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input)) {
7847 sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7848 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7849 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7850 }
7851
7852 // in case of an error, return discarded value
7853 if (sdp.is_errored()) {
7854 result = value_t::discarded;
7855 return;
7856 }
7857
7858 // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
7859 // function
7860 if (result.is_discarded()) {
7861 result = nullptr;
7862 }
7863 } else {
7864 json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
7865 sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
7866 result.assert_invariant();
7867
7868 // in strict mode, input must be completely read
7869 if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input)) {
7870 sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7871 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7872 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7873 }
7874
7875 // in case of an error, return discarded value
7876 if (sdp.is_errored()) {
7877 result = value_t::discarded;
7878 return;
7879 }
7880 }
7881 }
7882
7889 bool accept(const bool strict = true) {
7890 json_sax_acceptor<BasicJsonType> sax_acceptor;
7891 return sax_parse(&sax_acceptor, strict);
7892 }
7893
7894 template <typename SAX>
7895 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7896 bool sax_parse(SAX* sax, const bool strict = true) {
7897 (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType>{};
7898 const bool result = sax_parse_internal(sax);
7899
7900 // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
7901 if (result and strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input)) {
7902 return sax->parse_error(
7903 m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7904 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7905 }
7906
7907 return result;
7908 }
7909
7910private:
7911 template <typename SAX>
7912 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7913 bool sax_parse_internal(SAX* sax) {
7914 // stack to remember the hierarchy of structured values we are parsing
7915 // true = array; false = object
7916 std::vector<bool> states;
7917 // value to avoid a goto (see comment where set to true)
7918 bool skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
7919
7920 while (true) {
7921 if (not skip_to_state_evaluation) {
7922 // invariant: get_token() was called before each iteration
7923 switch (last_token) {
7924 case token_type::begin_object: {
7925 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1)))) {
7926 return false;
7927 }
7928
7929 // closing } -> we are done
7930 if (get_token() == token_type::end_object) {
7931 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object())) {
7932 return false;
7933 }
7934 break;
7935 }
7936
7937 // parse key
7938 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(last_token != token_type::value_string)) {
7939 return sax->parse_error(
7940 m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7941 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7942 exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
7943 }
7944 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string()))) {
7945 return false;
7946 }
7947
7948 // parse separator (:)
7949 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator)) {
7950 return sax->parse_error(
7951 m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7952 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7953 exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
7954 }
7955
7956 // remember we are now inside an object
7957 states.push_back(false);
7958
7959 // parse values
7960 get_token();
7961 continue;
7962 }
7963
7964 case token_type::begin_array: {
7965 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1)))) {
7966 return false;
7967 }
7968
7969 // closing ] -> we are done
7970 if (get_token() == token_type::end_array) {
7971 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array())) {
7972 return false;
7973 }
7974 break;
7975 }
7976
7977 // remember we are now inside an array
7978 states.push_back(true);
7979
7980 // parse values (no need to call get_token)
7981 continue;
7982 }
7983
7984 case token_type::value_float: {
7985 const auto res = m_lexer.get_number_float();
7986
7987 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(res))) {
7988 return sax->parse_error(
7989 m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7990 out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
7991 }
7992
7993 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_float(res, m_lexer.get_string()))) {
7994 return false;
7995 }
7996
7997 break;
7998 }
7999
8000 case token_type::literal_false: {
8001 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(false))) {
8002 return false;
8003 }
8004 break;
8005 }
8006
8007 case token_type::literal_null: {
8008 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->null())) {
8009 return false;
8010 }
8011 break;
8012 }
8013
8014 case token_type::literal_true: {
8015 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(true))) {
8016 return false;
8017 }
8018 break;
8019 }
8020
8021 case token_type::value_integer: {
8022 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_integer(m_lexer.get_number_integer()))) {
8023 return false;
8024 }
8025 break;
8026 }
8027
8028 case token_type::value_string: {
8029 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->string(m_lexer.get_string()))) {
8030 return false;
8031 }
8032 break;
8033 }
8034
8035 case token_type::value_unsigned: {
8036 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_unsigned(m_lexer.get_number_unsigned()))) {
8037 return false;
8038 }
8039 break;
8040 }
8041
8042 case token_type::parse_error: {
8043 // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
8044 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
8045 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
8046 exception_message(token_type::uninitialized, "value")));
8047 }
8048
8049 default: // the last token was unexpected
8050 {
8051 return sax->parse_error(
8052 m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
8053 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
8054 exception_message(token_type::literal_or_value, "value")));
8055 }
8056 }
8057 } else {
8058 skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
8059 }
8060
8061 // we reached this line after we successfully parsed a value
8062 if (states.empty()) {
8063 // empty stack: we reached the end of the hierarchy: done
8064 return true;
8065 }
8066
8067 if (states.back()) // array
8068 {
8069 // comma -> next value
8070 if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator) {
8071 // parse a new value
8072 get_token();
8073 continue;
8074 }
8075
8076 // closing ]
8077 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_array)) {
8078 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array())) {
8079 return false;
8080 }
8081
8082 // We are done with this array. Before we can parse a
8083 // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
8084 // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
8085 // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
8086 assert(not states.empty());
8087 states.pop_back();
8088 skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
8089 continue;
8090 }
8091
8092 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
8093 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
8094 exception_message(token_type::end_array, "array")));
8095 } else // object
8096 {
8097 // comma -> next value
8098 if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator) {
8099 // parse key
8100 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::value_string)) {
8101 return sax->parse_error(
8102 m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
8103 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
8104 exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
8105 }
8106
8107 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string()))) {
8108 return false;
8109 }
8110
8111 // parse separator (:)
8112 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator)) {
8113 return sax->parse_error(
8114 m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
8115 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
8116 exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
8117 }
8118
8119 // parse values
8120 get_token();
8121 continue;
8122 }
8123
8124 // closing }
8125 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_object)) {
8126 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object())) {
8127 return false;
8128 }
8129
8130 // We are done with this object. Before we can parse a
8131 // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
8132 // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
8133 // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
8134 assert(not states.empty());
8135 states.pop_back();
8136 skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
8137 continue;
8138 }
8139
8140 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(), m_lexer.get_token_string(),
8141 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
8142 exception_message(token_type::end_object, "object")));
8143 }
8144 }
8145 }
8146
8148 token_type get_token() { return last_token = m_lexer.scan(); }
8149
8150 std::string exception_message(const token_type expected, const std::string& context) {
8151 std::string error_msg = "syntax error ";
8152
8153 if (not context.empty()) {
8154 error_msg += "while parsing " + context + " ";
8155 }
8156
8157 error_msg += "- ";
8158
8159 if (last_token == token_type::parse_error) {
8160 error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
8161 } else {
8162 error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
8163 }
8164
8165 if (expected != token_type::uninitialized) {
8166 error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
8167 }
8168
8169 return error_msg;
8170 }
8171
8172private:
8174 const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
8176 token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
8178 lexer_t m_lexer;
8180 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
8181};
8182} // namespace detail
8183} // namespace nlohmann
8184
8185// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
8186
8187// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
8188
8189#include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
8190#include <limits> // numeric_limits
8191
8192namespace nlohmann {
8193namespace detail {
8194/*
8195@brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
8196
8197This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
8198string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
8199to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
8200a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
8201end_value (`1`) models past the end.
8202*/
8203class primitive_iterator_t {
8204private:
8205 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
8206 static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
8207 static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
8208
8210 difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
8211
8212public:
8213 constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept { return m_it; }
8214
8216 void set_begin() noexcept { m_it = begin_value; }
8217
8219 void set_end() noexcept { m_it = end_value; }
8220
8222 constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept { return m_it == begin_value; }
8223
8225 constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept { return m_it == end_value; }
8226
8227 friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept {
8228 return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
8229 }
8230
8231 friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept {
8232 return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
8233 }
8234
8235 primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept {
8236 auto result = *this;
8237 result += n;
8238 return result;
8239 }
8240
8241 friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept {
8242 return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
8243 }
8244
8245 primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept {
8246 ++m_it;
8247 return *this;
8248 }
8249
8250 primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int) noexcept {
8251 auto result = *this;
8252 ++m_it;
8253 return result;
8254 }
8255
8256 primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept {
8257 --m_it;
8258 return *this;
8259 }
8260
8261 primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int) noexcept {
8262 auto result = *this;
8263 --m_it;
8264 return result;
8265 }
8266
8267 primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept {
8268 m_it += n;
8269 return *this;
8270 }
8271
8272 primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept {
8273 m_it -= n;
8274 return *this;
8275 }
8276};
8277} // namespace detail
8278} // namespace nlohmann
8279
8280namespace nlohmann {
8281namespace detail {
8288template <typename BasicJsonType>
8289struct internal_iterator {
8291 typename BasicJsonType::object_t::iterator object_iterator{};
8293 typename BasicJsonType::array_t::iterator array_iterator{};
8295 primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator{};
8296};
8297} // namespace detail
8298} // namespace nlohmann

8303#include <iterator> // iterator, random_access_iterator_tag, bidirectional_iterator_tag, advance, next
8304#include <type_traits> // conditional, is_const, remove_const

8306// #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
8307
8308// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
8309

8320namespace nlohmann {
8321namespace detail {
8322// forward declare, to be able to friend it later on
8323template <typename IteratorType>
8324class iteration_proxy;
8325template <typename IteratorType>
8326class iteration_proxy_value;
8327
8344template <typename BasicJsonType>
8345class iter_impl {
8347 friend iter_impl<
8348 typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type,
8349 const BasicJsonType>::type>;
8350 friend BasicJsonType;
8351 friend iteration_proxy<iter_impl>;
8352 friend iteration_proxy_value<iter_impl>;
8353
8354 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
8355 using array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
8356 // make sure BasicJsonType is basic_json or const basic_json
8357 static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
8358 "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
8359
8360public:
8366 using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
8367
8369 using value_type = typename BasicJsonType::value_type;
8371 using difference_type = typename BasicJsonType::difference_type;
8373 using pointer =
8374 typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename BasicJsonType::const_pointer,
8375 typename BasicJsonType::pointer>::type;
8377 using reference =
8378 typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename BasicJsonType::const_reference,
8379 typename BasicJsonType::reference>::type;
8380
8382 iter_impl() = default;
8383
8390 explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object) {
8391 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8392
8393 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8394 case value_t::object: {
8395 m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
8396 break;
8397 }
8398
8399 case value_t::array: {
8400 m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
8401 break;
8402 }
8403
8404 default: {
8405 m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
8406 break;
8407 }
8408 }
8409 }
8410
8427 iter_impl(const iter_impl<const BasicJsonType>& other) noexcept : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it) {}
8428
8435 iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<const BasicJsonType>& other) noexcept {
8436 m_object = other.m_object;
8437 m_it = other.m_it;
8438 return *this;
8439 }
8440
8446 iter_impl(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
8447 : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it) {}
8448
8455 iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept {
8456 m_object = other.m_object;
8457 m_it = other.m_it;
8458 return *this;
8459 }
8460
8461private:
8466 void set_begin() noexcept {
8467 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8468
8469 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8470 case value_t::object: {
8471 m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
8472 break;
8473 }
8474
8475 case value_t::array: {
8476 m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
8477 break;
8478 }
8479
8480 case value_t::null: {
8481 // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
8482 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
8483 break;
8484 }
8485
8486 default: {
8487 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
8488 break;
8489 }
8490 }
8491 }
8492
8497 void set_end() noexcept {
8498 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8499
8500 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8501 case value_t::object: {
8502 m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
8503 break;
8504 }
8505
8506 case value_t::array: {
8507 m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
8508 break;
8509 }
8510
8511 default: {
8512 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
8513 break;
8514 }
8515 }
8516 }
8517
8518public:
8523 reference operator*() const {
8524 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8525
8526 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8527 case value_t::object: {
8528 assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
8529 return m_it.object_iterator->second;
8530 }
8531
8532 case value_t::array: {
8533 assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
8534 return *m_it.array_iterator;
8535 }
8536
8537 case value_t::null:
8538 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8539
8540 default: {
8541 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())) {
8542 return *m_object;
8543 }
8544
8545 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8546 }
8547 }
8548 }
8549
8554 pointer operator->() const {
8555 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8556
8557 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8558 case value_t::object: {
8559 assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
8560 return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
8561 }
8562
8563 case value_t::array: {
8564 assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
8565 return &*m_it.array_iterator;
8566 }
8567
8568 default: {
8569 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin())) {
8570 return m_object;
8571 }
8572
8573 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8574 }
8575 }
8576 }
8577
8582 iter_impl const operator++(int) {
8583 auto result = *this;
8584 ++(*this);
8585 return result;
8586 }
8587
8592 iter_impl& operator++() {
8593 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8594
8595 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8596 case value_t::object: {
8597 std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, 1);
8598 break;
8599 }
8600
8601 case value_t::array: {
8602 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
8603 break;
8604 }
8605
8606 default: {
8607 ++m_it.primitive_iterator;
8608 break;
8609 }
8610 }
8611
8612 return *this;
8613 }
8614
8619 iter_impl const operator--(int) {
8620 auto result = *this;
8621 --(*this);
8622 return result;
8623 }
8624
8629 iter_impl& operator--() {
8630 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8631
8632 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8633 case value_t::object: {
8634 std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
8635 break;
8636 }
8637
8638 case value_t::array: {
8639 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
8640 break;
8641 }
8642
8643 default: {
8644 --m_it.primitive_iterator;
8645 break;
8646 }
8647 }
8648
8649 return *this;
8650 }
8651
8656 bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const {
8657 // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8658 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object)) {
8659 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
8660 }
8661
8662 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8663
8664 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8665 case value_t::object:
8666 return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
8667
8668 case value_t::array:
8669 return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
8670
8671 default:
8672 return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8673 }
8674 }
8675
8680 bool operator!=(const iter_impl& other) const { return not operator==(other); }
8681
8686 bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const {
8687 // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8688 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object)) {
8689 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
8690 }
8691
8692 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8693
8694 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8695 case value_t::object:
8696 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(213, "cannot compare order of object iterators"));
8697
8698 case value_t::array:
8699 return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
8700
8701 default:
8702 return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8703 }
8704 }
8705
8710 bool operator<=(const iter_impl& other) const { return not other.operator<(*this); }
8711
8716 bool operator>(const iter_impl& other) const { return not operator<=(other); }
8717
8722 bool operator>=(const iter_impl& other) const { return not operator<(other); }
8723
8728 iter_impl& operator+=(difference_type i) {
8729 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8730
8731 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8732 case value_t::object:
8733 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
8734
8735 case value_t::array: {
8736 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, i);
8737 break;
8738 }
8739
8740 default: {
8741 m_it.primitive_iterator += i;
8742 break;
8743 }
8744 }
8745
8746 return *this;
8747 }
8748
8753 iter_impl& operator-=(difference_type i) { return operator+=(-i); }
8754
8759 iter_impl operator+(difference_type i) const {
8760 auto result = *this;
8761 result += i;
8762 return result;
8763 }
8764
8769 friend iter_impl operator+(difference_type i, const iter_impl& it) {
8770 auto result = it;
8771 result += i;
8772 return result;
8773 }
8774
8779 iter_impl operator-(difference_type i) const {
8780 auto result = *this;
8781 result -= i;
8782 return result;
8783 }
8784
8789 difference_type operator-(const iter_impl& other) const {
8790 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8791
8792 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8793 case value_t::object:
8794 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
8795
8796 case value_t::array:
8797 return m_it.array_iterator - other.m_it.array_iterator;
8798
8799 default:
8800 return m_it.primitive_iterator - other.m_it.primitive_iterator;
8801 }
8802 }
8803
8808 reference operator[](difference_type n) const {
8809 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8810
8811 switch (m_object->m_type) {
8812 case value_t::object:
8813 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(208, "cannot use operator[] for object iterators"));
8814
8815 case value_t::array:
8816 return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
8817
8818 case value_t::null:
8819 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8820
8821 default: {
8822 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.get_value() == -n)) {
8823 return *m_object;
8824 }
8825
8826 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8827 }
8828 }
8829 }
8830
8835 const typename object_t::key_type& key() const {
8836 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8837
8838 if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_object->is_object())) {
8839 return m_it.object_iterator->first;
8840 }
8841
8842 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(207, "cannot use key() for non-object iterators"));
8843 }
8844
8849 reference value() const { return operator*(); }
8850
8851private:
8853 pointer m_object = nullptr;
8855 internal_iterator<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type> m_it{};
8856};
8857} // namespace detail
8858} // namespace nlohmann

8892template <typename Base>
8893class json_reverse_iterator : public std::reverse_iterator<Base> {
8894public:
8895 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
8897 using base_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<Base>;
8899 using reference = typename Base::reference;
8900
8902 explicit json_reverse_iterator(const typename base_iterator::iterator_type& it) noexcept : base_iterator(it) {}
8903
8905 explicit json_reverse_iterator(const base_iterator& it) noexcept : base_iterator(it) {}
8906
8908 json_reverse_iterator const operator++(int) {
8909 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator++(1));
8910 }
8911
8913 json_reverse_iterator& operator++() { return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator++()); }
8914
8916 json_reverse_iterator const operator--(int) {
8917 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator--(1));
8918 }
8919
8921 json_reverse_iterator& operator--() { return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator--()); }
8922
8924 json_reverse_iterator& operator+=(difference_type i) {
8925 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator+=(i));
8926 }
8927
8929 json_reverse_iterator operator+(difference_type i) const {
8930 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator+(i));
8931 }
8932
8934 json_reverse_iterator operator-(difference_type i) const {
8935 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator-(i));
8936 }
8937
8939 difference_type operator-(const json_reverse_iterator& other) const {
8940 return base_iterator(*this) - base_iterator(other);
8941 }
8942
8944 reference operator[](difference_type n) const { return *(this->operator+(n)); }
8945
8947 auto key() const -> decltype(std::declval<Base>().key()) {
8948 auto it = --this->base();
8949 return it.key();
8950 }
8951
8953 reference value() const {
8954 auto it = --this->base();
8955 return it.operator*();
8956 }
8957};

8980template <typename BasicJsonType>
8981class json_pointer {
8982 // allow basic_json to access private members
8983 NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
8984 friend class basic_json;
8985
8986public:
9008 explicit json_pointer(const std::string& s = "") : reference_tokens(split(s)) {}
9009
9024 std::string to_string() const {
9025 return std::accumulate(reference_tokens.begin(), reference_tokens.end(), std::string{},
9026 [](const std::string& a, const std::string& b) { return a + "/" + escape(b); });
9027 }
9028
9030 operator std::string() const { return to_string(); }
9031
9048 json_pointer& operator/=(const json_pointer& ptr) {
9049 reference_tokens.insert(reference_tokens.end(), ptr.reference_tokens.begin(), ptr.reference_tokens.end());
9050 return *this;
9051 }
9052
9069 json_pointer& operator/=(std::string token) {
9070 push_back(std::move(token));
9071 return *this;
9072 }
9073
9090 json_pointer& operator/=(std::size_t array_index) { return *this /= std::to_string(array_index); }
9091
9107 friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& lhs, const json_pointer& rhs) { return json_pointer(lhs) /= rhs; }
9108
9124 friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& ptr, std::string token) {
9125 return json_pointer(ptr) /= std::move(token);
9126 }
9127
9143 friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& ptr, std::size_t array_index) {
9144 return json_pointer(ptr) /= array_index;
9145 }
9146
9160 json_pointer parent_pointer() const {
9161 if (empty()) {
9162 return *this;
9163 }
9164
9165 json_pointer res = *this;
9166 res.pop_back();
9167 return res;
9168 }
9169
9183 void pop_back() {
9184 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(empty())) {
9185 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
9186 }
9187
9188 reference_tokens.pop_back();
9189 }
9190
9205 const std::string& back() const {
9206 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(empty())) {
9207 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
9208 }
9209
9210 return reference_tokens.back();
9211 }
9212
9225 void push_back(const std::string& token) { reference_tokens.push_back(token); }
9226
9228 void push_back(std::string&& token) { reference_tokens.push_back(std::move(token)); }
9229
9244 bool empty() const noexcept { return reference_tokens.empty(); }
9245
9246private:
9254 static int array_index(const std::string& s) {
9255 std::size_t processed_chars = 0;
9256 const int res = std::stoi(s, &processed_chars);
9257
9258 // check if the string was completely read
9259 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(processed_chars != s.size())) {
9260 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + s + "'"));
9261 }
9262
9263 return res;
9264 }
9265
9266 json_pointer top() const {
9267 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(empty())) {
9268 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
9269 }
9270
9271 json_pointer result = *this;
9272 result.reference_tokens = {reference_tokens[0]};
9273 return result;
9274 }
9275
9284 BasicJsonType& get_and_create(BasicJsonType& j) const {
9285 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9286 auto result = &j;
9287
9288 // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the JSON value
9289 // j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
9290 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
9291 switch (result->type()) {
9292 case detail::value_t::null: {
9293 if (reference_token == "0") {
9294 // start a new array if reference token is 0
9295 result = &result->operator[](0);
9296 } else {
9297 // start a new object otherwise
9298 result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
9299 }
9300 break;
9301 }
9302
9303 case detail::value_t::object: {
9304 // create an entry in the object
9305 result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
9306 break;
9307 }
9308
9309 case detail::value_t::array: {
9310 // create an entry in the array
9311 JSON_TRY { result = &result->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token))); }
9312 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&) {
9313 JSON_THROW(
9314 detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9315 }
9316 break;
9317 }
9318
9319 /*
9320 The following code is only reached if there exists a reference
9321 token _and_ the current value is primitive. In this case, we have
9322 an error situation, because primitive values may only occur as
9323 single value; that is, with an empty list of reference tokens.
9324 */
9325 default:
9326 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(313, "invalid value to unflatten"));
9327 }
9328 }
9329
9330 return *result;
9331 }
9332
9352 BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const {
9353 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9354 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
9355 // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
9356 if (ptr->is_null()) {
9357 // check if reference token is a number
9358 const bool nums = std::all_of(reference_token.begin(), reference_token.end(),
9359 [](const unsigned char x) { return std::isdigit(x); });
9360
9361 // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object otherwise
9362 *ptr = (nums or reference_token == "-") ? detail::value_t::array : detail::value_t::object;
9363 }
9364
9365 switch (ptr->type()) {
9366 case detail::value_t::object: {
9367 // use unchecked object access
9368 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
9369 break;
9370 }
9371
9372 case detail::value_t::array: {
9373 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9374 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')) {
9375 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(
9376 106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
9377 }
9378
9379 if (reference_token == "-") {
9380 // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
9381 ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
9382 } else {
9383 // convert array index to number; unchecked access
9384 JSON_TRY { ptr = &ptr->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token))); }
9385 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&) {
9386 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(
9387 109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9388 }
9389 }
9390 break;
9391 }
9392
9393 default:
9394 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9395 }
9396 }
9397
9398 return *ptr;
9399 }
9400
9407 BasicJsonType& get_checked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const {
9408 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9409 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
9410 switch (ptr->type()) {
9411 case detail::value_t::object: {
9412 // note: at performs range check
9413 ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
9414 break;
9415 }
9416
9417 case detail::value_t::array: {
9418 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-")) {
9419 // "-" always fails the range check
9420 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(
9421 402, "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) + ") is out of range"));
9422 }
9423
9424 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9425 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')) {
9426 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(
9427 106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
9428 }
9429
9430 // note: at performs range check
9431 JSON_TRY { ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token))); }
9432 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&) {
9433 JSON_THROW(
9434 detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9435 }
9436 break;
9437 }
9438
9439 default:
9440 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9441 }
9442 }
9443
9444 return *ptr;
9445 }
9446
9460 const BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const {
9461 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9462 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
9463 switch (ptr->type()) {
9464 case detail::value_t::object: {
9465 // use unchecked object access
9466 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
9467 break;
9468 }
9469
9470 case detail::value_t::array: {
9471 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-")) {
9472 // "-" cannot be used for const access
9473 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(
9474 402, "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) + ") is out of range"));
9475 }
9476
9477 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9478 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')) {
9479 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(
9480 106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
9481 }
9482
9483 // use unchecked array access
9484 JSON_TRY { ptr = &ptr->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token))); }
9485 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&) {
9486 JSON_THROW(
9487 detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9488 }
9489 break;
9490 }
9491
9492 default:
9493 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9494 }
9495 }
9496
9497 return *ptr;
9498 }
9499
9506 const BasicJsonType& get_checked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const {
9507 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9508 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
9509 switch (ptr->type()) {
9510 case detail::value_t::object: {
9511 // note: at performs range check
9512 ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
9513 break;
9514 }
9515
9516 case detail::value_t::array: {
9517 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-")) {
9518 // "-" always fails the range check
9519 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(
9520 402, "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) + ") is out of range"));
9521 }
9522
9523 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9524 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')) {
9525 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(
9526 106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
9527 }
9528
9529 // note: at performs range check
9530 JSON_TRY { ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token))); }
9531 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&) {
9532 JSON_THROW(
9533 detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9534 }
9535 break;
9536 }
9537
9538 default:
9539 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9540 }
9541 }
9542
9543 return *ptr;
9544 }
9545
9550 bool contains(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const {
9551 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9552 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
9553 switch (ptr->type()) {
9554 case detail::value_t::object: {
9555 if (not ptr->contains(reference_token)) {
9556 // we did not find the key in the object
9557 return false;
9558 }
9559
9560 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
9561 break;
9562 }
9563
9564 case detail::value_t::array: {
9565 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-")) {
9566 // "-" always fails the range check
9567 return false;
9568 }
9569
9570 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9571 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0')) {
9572 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(
9573 106, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' must not begin with '0'"));
9574 }
9575
9576 JSON_TRY {
9577 const auto idx = static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token));
9578 if (idx >= ptr->size()) {
9579 // index out of range
9580 return false;
9581 }
9582
9583 ptr = &ptr->operator[](idx);
9584 break;
9585 }
9586 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&) {
9587 JSON_THROW(
9588 detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9589 }
9590 break;
9591 }
9592
9593 default: {
9594 // we do not expect primitive values if there is still a
9595 // reference token to process
9596 return false;
9597 }
9598 }
9599 }
9600
9601 // no reference token left means we found a primitive value
9602 return true;
9603 }
9604
9614 static std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string& reference_string) {
9615 std::vector<std::string> result;
9616
9617 // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
9618 if (reference_string.empty()) {
9619 return result;
9620 }
9621
9622 // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
9623 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_string[0] != '/')) {
9624 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(
9625 107, 1, "JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/' - was: '" + reference_string + "'"));
9626 }
9627
9628 // extract the reference tokens:
9629 // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
9630 // - start: position after the previous slash
9631 for (
9632 // search for the first slash after the first character
9633 std::size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
9634 // set the beginning of the first reference token
9635 start = 1;
9636 // we can stop if start == 0 (if slash == std::string::npos)
9637 start != 0;
9638 // set the beginning of the next reference token
9639 // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
9640 start = (slash == std::string::npos) ? 0 : slash + 1,
9641 // find next slash
9642 slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start)) {
9643 // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
9644 // (start) and the last slash (slash).
9645 auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
9646
9647 // check reference tokens are properly escaped
9648 for (std::size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~'); pos != std::string::npos;
9649 pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1)) {
9650 assert(reference_token[pos] == '~');
9651
9652 // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
9653 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(pos == reference_token.size() - 1 or
9654 (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' and reference_token[pos + 1] != '1'))) {
9655 JSON_THROW(
9656 detail::parse_error::create(108, 0, "escape character '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'"));
9657 }
9658 }
9659
9660 // finally, store the reference token
9661 unescape(reference_token);
9662 result.push_back(reference_token);
9663 }
9664
9665 return result;
9666 }
9667
9681 static void replace_substring(std::string& s, const std::string& f, const std::string& t) {
9682 assert(not f.empty());
9683 for (auto pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
9684 pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
9685 s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t, and
9686 pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size())) // find next occurrence of f
9687 {
9688 }
9689 }
9690
9692 static std::string escape(std::string s) {
9693 replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
9694 replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
9695 return s;
9696 }
9697
9699 static void unescape(std::string& s) {
9700 replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
9701 replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
9702 }
9703
9711 static void flatten(const std::string& reference_string, const BasicJsonType& value, BasicJsonType& result) {
9712 switch (value.type()) {
9713 case detail::value_t::array: {
9714 if (value.m_value.array->empty()) {
9715 // flatten empty array as null
9716 result[reference_string] = nullptr;
9717 } else {
9718 // iterate array and use index as reference string
9719 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i) {
9720 flatten(reference_string + "/" + std::to_string(i), value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
9721 }
9722 }
9723 break;
9724 }
9725
9726 case detail::value_t::object: {
9727 if (value.m_value.object->empty()) {
9728 // flatten empty object as null
9729 result[reference_string] = nullptr;
9730 } else {
9731 // iterate object and use keys as reference string
9732 for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object) {
9733 flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first), element.second, result);
9734 }
9735 }
9736 break;
9737 }
9738
9739 default: {
9740 // add primitive value with its reference string
9741 result[reference_string] = value;
9742 break;
9743 }
9744 }
9745 }
9746
9757 static BasicJsonType unflatten(const BasicJsonType& value) {
9758 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not value.is_object())) {
9759 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(314, "only objects can be unflattened"));
9760 }
9761
9762 BasicJsonType result;
9763
9764 // iterate the JSON object values
9765 for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object) {
9766 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(not element.second.is_primitive())) {
9767 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(315, "values in object must be primitive"));
9768 }
9769
9770 // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note that if
9771 // the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole value), function
9772 // get_and_create returns a reference to result itself. An assignment
9773 // will then create a primitive value.
9774 json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
9775 }
9776
9777 return result;
9778 }
9779
9791 friend bool operator==(json_pointer const& lhs, json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept {
9792 return lhs.reference_tokens == rhs.reference_tokens;
9793 }
9794
9806 friend bool operator!=(json_pointer const& lhs, json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept { return not(lhs == rhs); }
9807
9809 std::vector<std::string> reference_tokens;
9810};
9811} // namespace nlohmann
9812
9813// #include <nlohmann/detail/json_ref.hpp>
9814
9815#include <initializer_list>
9816#include <utility>
9817
9818// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/type_traits.hpp>
9819
9820namespace nlohmann {
9821namespace detail {
9822template <typename BasicJsonType>
9823class json_ref {
9824public:
9825 using value_type = BasicJsonType;
9826
9827 json_ref(value_type&& value) : owned_value(std::move(value)), value_ref(&owned_value), is_rvalue(true) {}
9828
9829 json_ref(const value_type& value) : value_ref(const_cast<value_type*>(&value)), is_rvalue(false) {}
9830
9831 json_ref(std::initializer_list<json_ref> init) : owned_value(init), value_ref(&owned_value), is_rvalue(true) {}
9832
9833 template <class... Args, enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<value_type, Args...>::value, int> = 0>
9834 json_ref(Args&&... args) : owned_value(std::forward<Args>(args)...), value_ref(&owned_value), is_rvalue(true) {}
9835
9836 // class should be movable only
9837 json_ref(json_ref&&) = default;
9838 json_ref(const json_ref&) = delete;
9839 json_ref& operator=(const json_ref&) = delete;
9840 json_ref& operator=(json_ref&&) = delete;
9841 ~json_ref() = default;
9842
9843 value_type moved_or_copied() const {
9844 if (is_rvalue) {
9845 return std::move(*value_ref);
9846 }
9847 return *value_ref;
9848 }
9849
9850 value_type const& operator*() const { return *static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref); }
9851
9852 value_type const* operator->() const { return static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref); }
9853
9854private:
9855 mutable value_type owned_value = nullptr;
9856 value_type* value_ref = nullptr;
9857 const bool is_rvalue;
9858};
9859} // namespace detail
9860} // namespace nlohmann

9893namespace nlohmann {
9894namespace detail {
9896template <typename CharType>
9897struct output_adapter_protocol {
9898 virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
9899 virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
9900 virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
9901};
9902
9904template <typename CharType>
9905using output_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<output_adapter_protocol<CharType>>;
9906
9908template <typename CharType>
9909class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType> {
9910public:
9911 explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) noexcept : v(vec) {}
9912
9913 void write_character(CharType c) override { v.push_back(c); }
9914
9915 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
9916 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override {
9917 std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
9918 }
9919
9920private:
9921 std::vector<CharType>& v;
9922};
9923
9925template <typename CharType>
9926class output_stream_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType> {
9927public:
9928 explicit output_stream_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) noexcept : stream(s) {}
9929
9930 void write_character(CharType c) override { stream.put(c); }
9931
9932 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
9933 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override {
9934 stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
9935 }
9936
9937private:
9938 std::basic_ostream<CharType>& stream;
9939};
9940
9942template <typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
9943class output_string_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType> {
9944public:
9945 explicit output_string_adapter(StringType& s) noexcept : str(s) {}
9946
9947 void write_character(CharType c) override { str.push_back(c); }
9948
9949 JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
9950 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override { str.append(s, length); }
9951
9952private:
9953 StringType& str;
9954};
9955
9956template <typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
9957class output_adapter {
9958public:
9959 output_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) : oa(std::make_shared<output_vector_adapter<CharType>>(vec)) {}
9960
9961 output_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) : oa(std::make_shared<output_stream_adapter<CharType>>(s)) {}
9962
9963 output_adapter(StringType& s) : oa(std::make_shared<output_string_adapter<CharType, StringType>>(s)) {}
9964
9965 operator output_adapter_t<CharType>() { return oa; }
9966
9967private:
9968 output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
9969};
9970} // namespace detail
9971} // namespace nlohmann
9972
9973namespace nlohmann {
9974namespace detail {
9976// binary writer //
9978
9982template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CharType>
9983class binary_writer {
9984 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
9985
9986public:
9992 explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<CharType> adapter) : oa(adapter) { assert(oa); }
9993
9998 void write_bson(const BasicJsonType& j) {
9999 switch (j.type()) {
10000 case value_t::object: {
10001 write_bson_object(*j.m_value.object);
10002 break;
10003 }
10004
10005 default: {
10006 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(317, "to serialize to BSON, top-level type must be object, but is " +
10007 std::string(j.type_name())));
10008 }
10009 }
10010 }
10011
10015 void write_cbor(const BasicJsonType& j) {
10016 switch (j.type()) {
10017 case value_t::null: {
10018 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xF6));
10019 break;
10020 }
10021
10022 case value_t::boolean: {
10023 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean ? to_char_type(0xF5) : to_char_type(0xF4));
10024 break;
10025 }
10026
10027 case value_t::number_integer: {
10028 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0) {
10029 // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
10030 // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
10031 // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
10032 if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17) {
10033 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10034 } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10035 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
10036 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10037 } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10038 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
10039 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10040 } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10041 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
10042 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10043 } else {
10044 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
10045 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10046 }
10047 } else {
10048 // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
10049 // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
10050 const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
10051 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24) {
10052 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
10053 } else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10054 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x38));
10055 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(positive_number));
10056 } else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10057 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x39));
10058 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(positive_number));
10059 } else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10060 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3A));
10061 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(positive_number));
10062 } else {
10063 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3B));
10064 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(positive_number));
10065 }
10066 }
10067 break;
10068 }
10069
10070 case value_t::number_unsigned: {
10071 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17) {
10072 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10073 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10074 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
10075 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10076 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10077 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
10078 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10079 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10080 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
10081 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10082 } else {
10083 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
10084 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
10085 }
10086 break;
10087 }
10088
10089 case value_t::number_float: {
10090 oa->write_character(get_cbor_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
10091 write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
10092 break;
10093 }
10094
10095 case value_t::string: {
10096 // step 1: write control byte and the string length
10097 const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
10098 if (N <= 0x17) {
10099 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
10100 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10101 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x78));
10102 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
10103 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10104 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x79));
10105 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10106 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10107 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7A));
10108 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10109 }
10110 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10111 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)()) {
10112 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7B));
10113 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
10114 }
10115 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10116
10117 // step 2: write the string
10118 oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10119 j.m_value.string->size());
10120 break;
10121 }
10122
10123 case value_t::array: {
10124 // step 1: write control byte and the array size
10125 const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
10126 if (N <= 0x17) {
10127 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
10128 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10129 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x98));
10130 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
10131 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10132 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x99));
10133 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10134 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10135 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9A));
10136 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10137 }
10138 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10139 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)()) {
10140 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9B));
10141 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
10142 }
10143 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10144
10145 // step 2: write each element
10146 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
10147 write_cbor(el);
10148 }
10149 break;
10150 }
10151
10152 case value_t::object: {
10153 // step 1: write control byte and the object size
10154 const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
10155 if (N <= 0x17) {
10156 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 + N));
10157 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10158 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB8));
10159 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
10160 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10161 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB9));
10162 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10163 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10164 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBA));
10165 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10166 }
10167 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10168 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)()) {
10169 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBB));
10170 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
10171 }
10172 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10173
10174 // step 2: write each element
10175 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
10176 write_cbor(el.first);
10177 write_cbor(el.second);
10178 }
10179 break;
10180 }
10181
10182 default:
10183 break;
10184 }
10185 }
10186
10190 void write_msgpack(const BasicJsonType& j) {
10191 switch (j.type()) {
10192 case value_t::null: // nil
10193 {
10194 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xC0));
10195 break;
10196 }
10197
10198 case value_t::boolean: // true and false
10199 {
10200 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean ? to_char_type(0xC3) : to_char_type(0xC2));
10201 break;
10202 }
10203
10204 case value_t::number_integer: {
10205 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0) {
10206 // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
10207 // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used
10208 // the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
10209 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128) {
10210 // positive fixnum
10211 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10212 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10213 // uint 8
10214 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
10215 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10216 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10217 // uint 16
10218 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
10219 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10220 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10221 // uint 32
10222 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
10223 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10224 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)()) {
10225 // uint 64
10226 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
10227 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10228 }
10229 } else {
10230 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32) {
10231 // negative fixnum
10232 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10233 } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() and
10234 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)()) {
10235 // int 8
10236 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD0));
10237 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10238 } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() and
10239 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)()) {
10240 // int 16
10241 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD1));
10242 write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10243 } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() and
10244 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()) {
10245 // int 32
10246 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD2));
10247 write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10248 } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() and
10249 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()) {
10250 // int 64
10251 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD3));
10252 write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10253 }
10254 }
10255 break;
10256 }
10257
10258 case value_t::number_unsigned: {
10259 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128) {
10260 // positive fixnum
10261 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10262 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10263 // uint 8
10264 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
10265 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10266 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10267 // uint 16
10268 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
10269 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10270 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10271 // uint 32
10272 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
10273 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10274 } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)()) {
10275 // uint 64
10276 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
10277 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10278 }
10279 break;
10280 }
10281
10282 case value_t::number_float: {
10283 oa->write_character(get_msgpack_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
10284 write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
10285 break;
10286 }
10287
10288 case value_t::string: {
10289 // step 1: write control byte and the string length
10290 const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
10291 if (N <= 31) {
10292 // fixstr
10293 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 | N));
10294 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()) {
10295 // str 8
10296 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD9));
10297 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
10298 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10299 // str 16
10300 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDA));
10301 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10302 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10303 // str 32
10304 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDB));
10305 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10306 }
10307
10308 // step 2: write the string
10309 oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10310 j.m_value.string->size());
10311 break;
10312 }
10313
10314 case value_t::array: {
10315 // step 1: write control byte and the array size
10316 const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
10317 if (N <= 15) {
10318 // fixarray
10319 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
10320 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10321 // array 16
10322 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDC));
10323 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10324 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10325 // array 32
10326 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDD));
10327 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10328 }
10329
10330 // step 2: write each element
10331 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
10332 write_msgpack(el);
10333 }
10334 break;
10335 }
10336
10337 case value_t::object: {
10338 // step 1: write control byte and the object size
10339 const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
10340 if (N <= 15) {
10341 // fixmap
10342 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xF)));
10343 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)()) {
10344 // map 16
10345 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDE));
10346 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10347 } else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)()) {
10348 // map 32
10349 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDF));
10350 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10351 }
10352
10353 // step 2: write each element
10354 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
10355 write_msgpack(el.first);
10356 write_msgpack(el.second);
10357 }
10358 break;
10359 }
10360
10361 default:
10362 break;
10363 }
10364 }
10365
10372 void write_ubjson(const BasicJsonType& j, const bool use_count, const bool use_type, const bool add_prefix = true) {
10373 switch (j.type()) {
10374 case value_t::null: {
10375 if (add_prefix) {
10376 oa->write_character(to_char_type('Z'));
10377 }
10378 break;
10379 }
10380
10381 case value_t::boolean: {
10382 if (add_prefix) {
10383 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean ? to_char_type('T') : to_char_type('F'));
10384 }
10385 break;
10386 }
10387
10388 case value_t::number_integer: {
10389 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_integer, add_prefix);
10390 break;
10391 }
10392
10393 case value_t::number_unsigned: {
10394 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_unsigned, add_prefix);
10395 break;
10396 }
10397
10398 case value_t::number_float: {
10399 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_float, add_prefix);
10400 break;
10401 }
10402
10403 case value_t::string: {
10404 if (add_prefix) {
10405 oa->write_character(to_char_type('S'));
10406 }
10407 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.string->size(), true);
10408 oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10409 j.m_value.string->size());
10410 break;
10411 }
10412
10413 case value_t::array: {
10414 if (add_prefix) {
10415 oa->write_character(to_char_type('['));
10416 }
10417
10418 bool prefix_required = true;
10419 if (use_type and not j.m_value.array->empty()) {
10420 assert(use_count);
10421 const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
10422 const bool same_prefix =
10423 std::all_of(j.begin() + 1, j.end(), [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType& v) {
10424 return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
10425 });
10426
10427 if (same_prefix) {
10428 prefix_required = false;
10429 oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
10430 oa->write_character(first_prefix);
10431 }
10432 }
10433
10434 if (use_count) {
10435 oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
10436 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.array->size(), true);
10437 }
10438
10439 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
10440 write_ubjson(el, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
10441 }
10442
10443 if (not use_count) {
10444 oa->write_character(to_char_type(']'));
10445 }
10446
10447 break;
10448 }
10449
10450 case value_t::object: {
10451 if (add_prefix) {
10452 oa->write_character(to_char_type('{'));
10453 }
10454
10455 bool prefix_required = true;
10456 if (use_type and not j.m_value.object->empty()) {
10457 assert(use_count);
10458 const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
10459 const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin(), j.end(), [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType& v) {
10460 return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
10461 });
10462
10463 if (same_prefix) {
10464 prefix_required = false;
10465 oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
10466 oa->write_character(first_prefix);
10467 }
10468 }
10469
10470 if (use_count) {
10471 oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
10472 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.object->size(), true);
10473 }
10474
10475 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
10476 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(el.first.size(), true);
10477 oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(el.first.c_str()), el.first.size());
10478 write_ubjson(el.second, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
10479 }
10480
10481 if (not use_count) {
10482 oa->write_character(to_char_type('}'));
10483 }
10484
10485 break;
10486 }
10487
10488 default:
10489 break;
10490 }
10491 }
10492
10493private:
10495 // BSON //
10497
10502 static std::size_t calc_bson_entry_header_size(const string_t& name) {
10503 const auto it = name.find(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0));
10504 if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(it != BasicJsonType::string_t::npos)) {
10505 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(409, "BSON key cannot contain code point U+0000 (at byte " +
10506 std::to_string(it) + ")"));
10507 }
10508
10509 return /*id*/ 1ul + name.size() + /*zero-terminator*/ 1u;
10510 }
10511
10515 void write_bson_entry_header(const string_t& name, const std::uint8_t element_type) {
10516 oa->write_character(to_char_type(element_type)); // boolean
10517 oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(name.c_str()), name.size() + 1u);
10518 }
10519
10523 void write_bson_boolean(const string_t& name, const bool value) {
10524 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x08);
10525 oa->write_character(value ? to_char_type(0x01) : to_char_type(0x00));
10526 }
10527
10531 void write_bson_double(const string_t& name, const double value) {
10532 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x01);
10533 write_number<double, true>(value);
10534 }
10535
10539 static std::size_t calc_bson_string_size(const string_t& value) {
10540 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + value.size() + 1ul;
10541 }
10542
10546 void write_bson_string(const string_t& name, const string_t& value) {
10547 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x02);
10548
10549 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value.size() + 1ul));
10550 oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(value.c_str()), value.size() + 1);
10551 }
10552
10556 void write_bson_null(const string_t& name) { write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x0A); }
10557
10561 static std::size_t calc_bson_integer_size(const std::int64_t value) {
10562 return (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value and
10563 value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()
10564 ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
10565 : sizeof(std::int64_t);
10566 }
10567
10571 void write_bson_integer(const string_t& name, const std::int64_t value) {
10572 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value and
10573 value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()) {
10574 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10); // int32
10575 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
10576 } else {
10577 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12); // int64
10578 write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
10579 }
10580 }
10581
10585 static constexpr std::size_t calc_bson_unsigned_size(const std::uint64_t value) noexcept {
10586 return (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())) ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
10587 : sizeof(std::int64_t);
10588 }
10589
10593 void write_bson_unsigned(const string_t& name, const std::uint64_t value) {
10594 if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())) {
10595 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10 /* int32 */);
10596 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
10597 } else if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())) {
10598 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12 /* int64 */);
10599 write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
10600 } else {
10601 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(value) +
10602 " cannot be represented by BSON as it does not fit int64"));
10603 }
10604 }
10605
10609 void write_bson_object_entry(const string_t& name, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value) {
10610 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x03); // object
10611 write_bson_object(value);
10612 }
10613
10617 static std::size_t calc_bson_array_size(const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value) {
10618 std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
10619
10620 const std::size_t embedded_document_size =
10621 std::accumulate(std::begin(value), std::end(value), 0ul,
10622 [&array_index](std::size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::array_t::value_type& el) {
10623 return result + calc_bson_element_size(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
10624 });
10625
10626 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + embedded_document_size + 1ul;
10627 }
10628
10632 void write_bson_array(const string_t& name, const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value) {
10633 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x04); // array
10634 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_array_size(value)));
10635
10636 std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
10637
10638 for (const auto& el : value) {
10639 write_bson_element(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
10640 }
10641
10642 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
10643 }
10644
10649 static std::size_t calc_bson_element_size(const string_t& name, const BasicJsonType& j) {
10650 const auto header_size = calc_bson_entry_header_size(name);
10651 switch (j.type()) {
10652 case value_t::object:
10653 return header_size + calc_bson_object_size(*j.m_value.object);
10654
10655 case value_t::array:
10656 return header_size + calc_bson_array_size(*j.m_value.array);
10657
10658 case value_t::boolean:
10659 return header_size + 1ul;
10660
10661 case value_t::number_float:
10662 return header_size + 8ul;
10663
10664 case value_t::number_integer:
10665 return header_size + calc_bson_integer_size(j.m_value.number_integer);
10666
10667 case value_t::number_unsigned:
10668 return header_size + calc_bson_unsigned_size(j.m_value.number_unsigned);
10669
10670 case value_t::string:
10671 return header_size + calc_bson_string_size(*j.m_value.string);
10672
10673 case value_t::null:
10674 return header_size + 0ul;
10675
10676 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10677 default:
10678 assert(false);
10679 return 0ul;
10680 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10681 }
10682 }
10683
10691 void write_bson_element(const string_t& name, const BasicJsonType& j) {
10692 switch (j.type()) {
10693 case value_t::object:
10694 return write_bson_object_entry(name, *j.m_value.object);
10695
10696 case value_t::array:
10697 return write_bson_array(name, *j.m_value.array);
10698
10699 case value_t::boolean:
10700 return write_bson_boolean(name, j.m_value.boolean);
10701
10702 case value_t::number_float:
10703 return write_bson_double(name, j.m_value.number_float);
10704
10705 case value_t::number_integer:
10706 return write_bson_integer(name, j.m_value.number_integer);
10707
10708 case value_t::number_unsigned:
10709 return write_bson_unsigned(name, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
10710
10711 case value_t::string:
10712 return write_bson_string(name, *j.m_value.string);
10713
10714 case value_t::null:
10715 return write_bson_null(name);
10716
10717 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10718 default:
10719 assert(false);
10720 return;
10721 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10722 }
10723 }
10724
10731 static std::size_t calc_bson_object_size(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value) {
10732 std::size_t document_size = std::accumulate(
10733 value.begin(), value.end(), 0ul, [](size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type& el) {
10734 return result += calc_bson_element_size(el.first, el.second);
10735 });
10736
10737 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + document_size + 1ul;
10738 }
10739
10744 void write_bson_object(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value) {
10745 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_object_size(value)));
10746
10747 for (const auto& el : value) {
10748 write_bson_element(el.first, el.second);
10749 }
10750
10751 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
10752 }
